1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,900
I've  heard  stories,  but  I  never  imagined  it  would  be  like

2
00:00:02,900 --> 00:00:03,560
this.

3
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:05,320
This place holds secrets.

4
00:00:06,520 --> 00:00:07,660
I know it.

5
00:00:09,510 --> 00:00:09,990
Chapter 1.

6
00:00:10,190 --> 00:00:11,230
An ordinary Tuesday

7
00:00:12,310 --> 00:00:14,910
The house near the Savannah River woke up slowly.

8
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:18,770
The  way  old  houses  do,  carrying  the  habit  of  breathing  before

9
00:00:18,770 --> 00:00:19,450
their  people.

10
00:00:19,870 --> 00:00:23,210
The  light  of  dawn  came  through  the  crack  in  the  curtains  in  a  thin  strip

11
00:00:23,210 --> 00:00:24,210
and  settled  on

12
00:00:24,210 --> 00:00:27,350
her  shoulder,  and  Jago  Quint  stood  there  looking  at  that

13
00:00:27,350 --> 00:00:28,510
shoulder  for  longer  than  was

14
00:00:28,510 --> 00:00:29,030
reasonable.

15
00:00:29,610 --> 00:00:32,650
Rowena  slept  on  her  side,  one  hand  opened  near  her

16
00:00:32,650 --> 00:00:34,630
face,  like  someone  who  had  left  a  question

17
00:00:34,630 --> 00:00:37,770
half-assed, and decided to finish asking at the next day.

18
00:00:38,150 --> 00:00:41,150
The  sheet  had  slipped  down  to  her  waist,  and  the  light  caught

19
00:00:41,150 --> 00:00:42,470
the  loose  strands  of  her  hair

20
00:00:42,470 --> 00:00:44,790
which still smelled of the soap from the night before.

21
00:00:45,210 --> 00:00:46,590
He got up without a sound.

22
00:00:47,110 --> 00:00:48,510
His body knew this ritual.

23
00:00:48,990 --> 00:00:51,310
Getting out of bed without waking the one who stayed.

24
00:00:51,770 --> 00:00:54,190
There was a calm inside him that still scared him.

25
00:00:54,510 --> 00:00:56,470
Six months after she'd moved into that house.

26
00:00:56,470 --> 00:00:59,550
That  was  love  he'd  discovered,  and  at  the  same  time  it

27
00:00:59,550 --> 00:01:01,090
was  something  else  a  small  dread,

28
00:01:01,570 --> 00:01:05,470
almost decorative that lived beneath his ribcage and beat along with his heart.

29
00:01:05,910 --> 00:01:07,370
He thought he knew how to handle it.

30
00:01:07,690 --> 00:01:11,470
A man who survived what he'd survived, learns to tame his own fear.

31
00:01:11,870 --> 00:01:14,910
He went down the stairs stepping on the side of the wood that didn't creak.

32
00:01:15,290 --> 00:01:20,050
The kitchen was still cold, with that stale air of June mornings that hadn't decided

33
00:01:20,050 --> 00:01:21,550
whether they were warm or not.

34
00:01:21,750 --> 00:01:22,730
He turned on the kettle.

35
00:01:22,730 --> 00:01:26,970
Measured out her coffee like someone writing a sentence he already knew by heart.

36
00:01:27,450 --> 00:01:32,610
Two scoops of grounds, water that hadn't fully boiled, a little less than the usual ratio,

37
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:36,110
because Roenah liked her coffee milder at the start of the day,

38
00:01:36,490 --> 00:01:39,410
as if the morning needed to ask permission before coming in.

39
00:01:39,890 --> 00:01:41,870
The smell rose slowly through the kitchen.

40
00:01:42,350 --> 00:01:44,490
There was something in it he could never quite name.

41
00:01:44,890 --> 00:01:46,230
It wasn't the coffee itself.

42
00:01:46,630 --> 00:01:48,250
It was what the smell stood for.

43
00:01:48,550 --> 00:01:50,370
She was still there and she'd come down.

44
00:01:50,370 --> 00:01:54,410
There was a thought he avoided at that hour, and the thought showed up anyway.

45
00:01:54,830 --> 00:01:59,410
If she ever vanished from there, the smell of coffee would tear him apart with devastating efficiency.

46
00:02:00,030 --> 00:02:06,290
He stirred the spoon slowly and brushed the thought aside with the same gesture you'd use to wave off a polite fly.

47
00:02:06,750 --> 00:02:07,310
Not today.

48
00:02:07,810 --> 00:02:08,790
The male came early.

49
00:02:09,290 --> 00:02:14,270
Feline, the personal assistant, delivered the envelope at the side door with the discrete punctuality

50
00:02:14,270 --> 00:02:15,630
J. Gope de Léfour.

51
00:02:16,030 --> 00:02:19,710
There were three letters from the office, one from the management of one of the properties,

52
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:22,810
and a cream-coloured envelope, no return address,

53
00:02:23,370 --> 00:02:26,510
a dress to Roenah Pike in the impersonal handwriting of a secretary,

54
00:02:27,110 --> 00:02:28,590
at some respectable institution.

55
00:02:29,230 --> 00:02:32,650
He recognized the letterhead in the upper corner before he even looked properly.

56
00:02:33,230 --> 00:02:35,910
He stood there for a second with the envelope between his fingers,

57
00:02:36,410 --> 00:02:38,670
feeling the specific weight of quality paper.

58
00:02:39,190 --> 00:02:41,390
I'll take this one. He said, low.

59
00:02:41,850 --> 00:02:44,590
He tucked the envelope into the inside pocket of his jacket,

60
00:02:45,050 --> 00:02:48,650
as if he were putting away an important document he'd remember to hand over later.

61
00:02:48,650 --> 00:02:54,390
He knew he wouldn't remember. He'd already decided not to remember before he even finished the gesture.

62
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:58,250
The worst part was that his hand had made the move without consulting him,

63
00:02:58,490 --> 00:03:02,530
with an old efficiency he recognized as his own and didn't like recognizing.

64
00:03:03,250 --> 00:03:04,210
Feline saw it.

65
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:05,450
Feline said nothing.

66
00:03:05,990 --> 00:03:10,470
The two exchanged a brief greeting, and the assistant left the same way he'd come in,

67
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:12,830
is steps muffled by the runner in the hallway.

68
00:03:13,330 --> 00:03:16,550
When Roenah came down, coffee was served in two cups.

69
00:03:16,550 --> 00:03:20,270
She appeared in the kitchen doorway in a long night gown.

70
00:03:20,670 --> 00:03:24,910
Her hair loosely pinned up, rubbing her eye with a closed fist like a child.

71
00:03:25,390 --> 00:03:27,910
The morning sun was coming in now through the side window,

72
00:03:28,430 --> 00:03:31,410
and drew a golden square on the wooden floor between them.

73
00:03:31,590 --> 00:03:35,670
He looked up and the small decorative dread settled back beneath his ribcage quiet.

74
00:03:36,190 --> 00:03:36,830
You got up early?

75
00:03:37,270 --> 00:03:39,670
She remarked, her voice still thick with sleep.

76
00:03:40,070 --> 00:03:42,730
I couldn't sleep with you breathing so beautifully like that,

77
00:03:42,730 --> 00:03:45,630
J. Go answered, and his mouth almost smiled.

78
00:03:46,130 --> 00:03:46,670
She laughed.

79
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:52,270
It was a short slightly husky laugh, the kind he collected inside without admitting he collected them.

80
00:03:52,470 --> 00:03:56,190
She sat on the stool at the kitchen island, took the cup with both hands,

81
00:03:56,570 --> 00:03:59,470
and smelled it before drinking the way she did every day,

82
00:03:59,850 --> 00:04:02,290
her eyes closing for half a second over the steam,

83
00:04:02,890 --> 00:04:05,590
a gesture so hers that he already knew it by heart.

84
00:04:05,950 --> 00:04:07,550
He watched without seeming to watch.

85
00:04:08,010 --> 00:04:09,510
Are you expecting anything today?

86
00:04:09,510 --> 00:04:13,090
He asked, and the tone was casual in that practiced way,

87
00:04:13,470 --> 00:04:16,010
rowing a thought for a second her eyes still on the cup,

88
00:04:16,310 --> 00:04:17,610
an answer, she said,

89
00:04:17,990 --> 00:04:18,270
maybe.

90
00:04:18,690 --> 00:04:22,050
That conversation I told you about last week, she looked up.

91
00:04:22,250 --> 00:04:22,850
You remember?

92
00:04:23,390 --> 00:04:24,850
I remember, he answered.

93
00:04:25,370 --> 00:04:25,850
You remembered?

94
00:04:26,390 --> 00:04:29,590
In his pocket he had exactly the answer she was waiting for,

95
00:04:29,750 --> 00:04:30,970
and the answer was generous.

96
00:04:31,510 --> 00:04:34,150
And the answer would take her out of that house for six months.

97
00:04:34,670 --> 00:04:36,870
The pocket weighed on him in a specific way.

98
00:04:36,870 --> 00:04:39,610
He drank his own coffee and said nothing more.

99
00:04:40,050 --> 00:04:42,430
Rowena looked at him for a second longer than her usual,

100
00:04:42,890 --> 00:04:44,370
then she looked at her own coffee,

101
00:04:44,810 --> 00:04:46,830
and the rest of the morning ran along beautifully,

102
00:04:47,430 --> 00:04:49,250
the way their mornings usually ran.

103
00:04:49,730 --> 00:04:53,830
At noon, Silas Ashford was waiting for Jago at the office in downtown Savannah.

104
00:04:54,310 --> 00:04:58,010
The lawyer had a way of sitting in chairs that didn't belong to him as if they did.

105
00:04:58,330 --> 00:05:01,190
Legs crossed, one finger resting against his temple,

106
00:05:01,710 --> 00:05:04,490
the expressionless face he wore when he brought bad news.

107
00:05:04,490 --> 00:05:07,210
The air conditioning in the room was set too high,

108
00:05:07,630 --> 00:05:12,290
and the artificial chill clashed with the heat coming in through the wide windows overlooking the square.

109
00:05:12,930 --> 00:05:15,810
Short lunch, Silas announced when Jago walked in.

110
00:05:16,190 --> 00:05:16,730
Short why?

111
00:05:17,270 --> 00:05:19,910
Because what I've got to tell you doesn't go well with dessert.

112
00:05:20,490 --> 00:05:24,210
Jago closed the door behind him, he sat down on the other side of the desk.

113
00:05:24,630 --> 00:05:27,150
The two had known each other long enough to skip the run around.

114
00:05:27,750 --> 00:05:30,990
Someone's asking questions, Silas said without raising his voice,

115
00:05:30,990 --> 00:05:33,010
again in three different places,

116
00:05:33,590 --> 00:05:36,170
discrete questions, the kind of trained person asks,

117
00:05:36,750 --> 00:05:40,550
and the questions come too close to what we agreed to never let anyone get close to.

118
00:05:40,730 --> 00:05:44,290
Jago didn't move, inside the decorative dread grew an inch.

119
00:05:44,830 --> 00:05:45,110
Name?

120
00:05:45,730 --> 00:05:50,370
He asked, not yet, but they pay well, and they pay with money that leaves no trail.

121
00:05:50,750 --> 00:05:52,370
That interest me more than the name.

122
00:05:52,770 --> 00:05:53,990
Jago looked at the desk.

123
00:05:54,370 --> 00:05:56,710
There was a line of silence the two of them respected,

124
00:05:57,290 --> 00:05:59,130
the kind built over years of loyalty,

125
00:05:59,130 --> 00:06:00,390
Silas waited.

126
00:06:00,870 --> 00:06:03,550
He always waited with that stone patience he charged

127
00:06:03,550 --> 00:06:05,050
dearly for by the hour.

128
00:06:05,310 --> 00:06:08,230
Double the security at the house, Jago said finally.

129
00:06:09,070 --> 00:06:09,630
Quietly.

130
00:06:10,010 --> 00:06:11,070
Rowina can't know.

131
00:06:11,510 --> 00:06:13,730
Silas kept looking at him a second longer than necessary.

132
00:06:14,370 --> 00:06:16,470
Jago, she can't know Silas.

133
00:06:16,970 --> 00:06:19,910
The lawyer ran his tongue along the inside corner of his cheek,

134
00:06:20,290 --> 00:06:22,730
a small gesture he made when he wanted to say something,

135
00:06:23,150 --> 00:06:24,030
and chose not to.

136
00:06:24,390 --> 00:06:27,150
Then he nodded in that short dry way of his.

137
00:06:27,150 --> 00:06:29,510
And that envelope, Silas asked,

138
00:06:29,970 --> 00:06:30,990
did the answer come?

139
00:06:31,490 --> 00:06:32,990
Jago didn't answer right away.

140
00:06:33,310 --> 00:06:36,370
He tapped his thumb lightly on the tabletop once twice.

141
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:37,490
It came.

142
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:39,150
Are you going to deliver it?

143
00:06:39,410 --> 00:06:39,970
I am.

144
00:06:40,310 --> 00:06:40,510
When?

145
00:06:41,110 --> 00:06:42,010
Jago looked up.

146
00:06:42,250 --> 00:06:45,610
There was something in his eyes that Silas had known long before this conversation.

147
00:06:46,170 --> 00:06:48,850
The same thing that lived in that gaze ten years ago,

148
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:52,110
and that Silas had hoped for a while had gotten better.

149
00:06:52,450 --> 00:06:55,050
When I figure out how, Silas nodded,

150
00:06:55,350 --> 00:06:56,490
but his face didn't agree.

151
00:06:56,490 --> 00:07:00,210
The two finished lunch in decent silence with the noise from the square

152
00:07:00,210 --> 00:07:01,790
coming in muffled through the windows.

153
00:07:02,330 --> 00:07:03,550
When Jago left the office,

154
00:07:04,010 --> 00:07:07,230
the cream envelope was still weighing in the inside pocket of his jacket,

155
00:07:07,650 --> 00:07:12,310
and he had for the first time in a long time, a brief urge to tear it up.

156
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:15,610
Rowina spent the afternoon in the living room of the house near the river.

157
00:07:16,030 --> 00:07:17,910
She was rereading some old worknotes,

158
00:07:18,290 --> 00:07:21,850
things she kept in a hardcover folder that sat on a shelf in plain sight,

159
00:07:22,250 --> 00:07:23,490
no hiding place at all.

160
00:07:23,490 --> 00:07:26,790
She'd learned to value that transparency the way people do,

161
00:07:27,070 --> 00:07:29,690
who have already lost someone by hiding too much.

162
00:07:29,970 --> 00:07:33,530
The afternoon light came in slanted through the half open blinds,

163
00:07:33,530 --> 00:07:35,470
and striped the rug in golden bands.

164
00:07:35,990 --> 00:07:38,590
Outside the river made its usual gentle sound,

165
00:07:39,050 --> 00:07:41,490
the living room phone rang at a little past five.

166
00:07:41,930 --> 00:07:43,650
Neither he'd gone to the market with Fielen.

167
00:07:44,250 --> 00:07:45,790
Jago hadn't come back yet.

168
00:07:46,250 --> 00:07:46,950
Rowina answered.

169
00:07:47,430 --> 00:07:48,110
Quint residence.

170
00:07:48,710 --> 00:07:49,070
She said.

171
00:07:49,430 --> 00:07:50,590
The way she always answered,

172
00:07:50,990 --> 00:07:52,430
half joking with the formality.

173
00:07:52,430 --> 00:07:55,610
On the other end, a full second of silence.

174
00:07:56,130 --> 00:07:59,050
Then a man's voice horse with age and with something harder to name,

175
00:07:59,530 --> 00:08:01,390
good afternoon I need to speak with Mr. Quint.

176
00:08:01,930 --> 00:08:04,030
He's not in at the moment, can I take a message?

177
00:08:04,630 --> 00:08:05,330
Another silence.

178
00:08:05,990 --> 00:08:09,430
She heard the man breathe as if he were weighing every word before letting it out.

179
00:08:09,910 --> 00:08:11,690
Rowina, a well-trained journalist,

180
00:08:12,150 --> 00:08:14,230
began paying attention with her whole body,

181
00:08:14,690 --> 00:08:15,950
without yet knowing why.

182
00:08:16,390 --> 00:08:19,010
There was something in that silence that wasn't in decision.

183
00:08:19,570 --> 00:08:20,610
It was calculation.

184
00:08:21,370 --> 00:08:23,210
It's the man coughed lightly.

185
00:08:23,730 --> 00:08:24,730
It's about kit.

186
00:08:25,070 --> 00:08:26,530
Tell him it's about kit.

187
00:08:26,930 --> 00:08:27,690
He'll understand.

188
00:08:28,370 --> 00:08:29,970
Rowina stopped breathing for a second.

189
00:08:30,490 --> 00:08:31,630
Not because of the name.

190
00:08:32,050 --> 00:08:33,790
The name still meant nothing to her.

191
00:08:33,950 --> 00:08:36,110
She stopped because of the way the man said it.

192
00:08:36,410 --> 00:08:38,010
Like someone handing over a password,

193
00:08:38,210 --> 00:08:40,870
he knows will open a door that's been locked for a long time.

194
00:08:41,430 --> 00:08:42,970
Kit, she repeated slowly,

195
00:08:43,370 --> 00:08:45,830
and her voice came out more neutral than she was feeling.

196
00:08:46,430 --> 00:08:47,610
May I ask who's calling?

197
00:08:47,610 --> 00:08:50,670
The man was already answering when the front door slammed.

198
00:08:51,350 --> 00:08:52,250
Quick steps in the hallway.

199
00:08:52,730 --> 00:08:55,370
Quicker than Jago's step usually was at the end of the day.

200
00:08:55,690 --> 00:08:58,750
He walked into the room with his meeting posture still in his body,

201
00:08:59,130 --> 00:09:01,490
and stopped walking when he saw the phone in her hand.

202
00:09:01,910 --> 00:09:05,270
She watched the colour drain from his face in real time.

203
00:09:05,570 --> 00:09:08,310
It was something she'd never seen before in that man.

204
00:09:08,810 --> 00:09:11,010
No anger, no practice surprise,

205
00:09:11,570 --> 00:09:13,610
just a physical animal whiteness,

206
00:09:13,830 --> 00:09:16,150
rising from his chin to his forehead in seconds,

207
00:09:16,150 --> 00:09:18,210
as if someone had flipped a switch.

208
00:09:18,730 --> 00:09:19,390
Who is it?

209
00:09:19,630 --> 00:09:22,750
He asked, his voice too low for the size of the question.

210
00:09:23,290 --> 00:09:24,310
Roena didn't answer.

211
00:09:24,770 --> 00:09:25,670
She held out the receiver.

212
00:09:26,330 --> 00:09:27,970
Jago took it, brought it to his ear,

213
00:09:27,990 --> 00:09:30,850
listened for two seconds, closed his eyes once,

214
00:09:31,310 --> 00:09:33,070
a single blink longer than normal.

215
00:09:33,510 --> 00:09:35,990
The kind of gesture that isn't reflex its decision,

216
00:09:36,570 --> 00:09:38,030
and then said just one sentence.

217
00:09:38,590 --> 00:09:39,670
Don't call this number.

218
00:09:40,110 --> 00:09:40,750
He hung up.

219
00:09:40,970 --> 00:09:44,990
He kept his hand on the phone for a length of time she counted inside her own chest,

220
00:09:44,990 --> 00:09:47,890
beat by beat, Roena looked at him.

221
00:09:48,130 --> 00:09:49,690
She knew that man in her body,

222
00:09:49,990 --> 00:09:53,770
in his smell, in the way he ran his thumb under his eye when he was tired.

223
00:09:54,250 --> 00:09:55,990
She'd never seen him white like that.

224
00:09:56,190 --> 00:09:58,770
She'd never seen him need support just to stay standing.

225
00:09:59,430 --> 00:10:01,710
Jago, he didn't answer right away.

226
00:10:01,910 --> 00:10:02,530
Who was it?

227
00:10:02,730 --> 00:10:06,490
She asked, with the trained calm her profession had given her as a gift.

228
00:10:06,990 --> 00:10:09,530
He looked up, and that was when she saw it.

229
00:10:09,750 --> 00:10:11,750
But the first time since the two of them had met,

230
00:10:12,050 --> 00:10:13,650
she saw him decide to lie.

231
00:10:13,650 --> 00:10:15,370
It wasn't a quick decision.

232
00:10:15,850 --> 00:10:17,350
She saw the moment before it,

233
00:10:17,490 --> 00:10:20,130
the instant when he could still choose the other path.

234
00:10:20,410 --> 00:10:22,310
An old employee, Jago said,

235
00:10:22,650 --> 00:10:24,670
drunk probably got the wrong number.

236
00:10:24,990 --> 00:10:26,270
She kept looking at him.

237
00:10:26,470 --> 00:10:30,330
He held her gaze with the composure of someone who'd spent his whole life holding gays,

238
00:10:30,690 --> 00:10:32,130
he couldn't afford to lose.

239
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:34,670
He knew inside that she knew.

240
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,390
Still, he wanted her to let it go.

241
00:10:37,770 --> 00:10:39,470
He said a name, Roena said,

242
00:10:39,930 --> 00:10:42,310
and her voice came out very low almost gentle,

243
00:10:42,310 --> 00:10:45,130
which was the way she used when the question wasn't gentle.

244
00:10:45,770 --> 00:10:46,330
Jago swallowed.

245
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:47,350
What name?

246
00:10:48,650 --> 00:10:49,270
He didn't blink.

247
00:10:49,730 --> 00:10:52,310
He carried his body to the sideboard next to the sofa,

248
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:55,370
rested his hand on the wood as if he needed something solid,

249
00:10:55,890 --> 00:10:58,070
and spoke looking at the river through the window,

250
00:10:58,470 --> 00:10:59,390
his back to her.

251
00:10:59,550 --> 00:11:00,730
I don't know him.

252
00:11:01,070 --> 00:11:02,390
Roena stood where she was.

253
00:11:02,830 --> 00:11:05,710
On the other side of the room near the big window there was a chair.

254
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:08,290
Just like the one in the mansions main hall,

255
00:11:08,710 --> 00:11:10,250
brought here when they moved in.

256
00:11:10,250 --> 00:11:14,150
She had now six months of looking at that chair without understanding why no

257
00:11:14,150 --> 00:11:15,350
one ever sat in it.

258
00:11:15,550 --> 00:11:18,070
Why the seat was always turned slightly toward the river,

259
00:11:18,510 --> 00:11:21,270
as if waiting for someone who knew where they'd arrive from.

260
00:11:21,470 --> 00:11:24,250
She looked at the chair, looked at Jago's back,

261
00:11:24,530 --> 00:11:25,770
looked at the chair again,

262
00:11:26,030 --> 00:11:28,310
and the chair for the first time had a sound.

263
00:11:28,830 --> 00:11:31,610
The name was short, short, and old.

264
00:11:32,030 --> 00:11:35,970
It had only three letters, and had slipped down the phone line like a poorly tied

265
00:11:35,970 --> 00:11:38,250
secret, spoken by a horse voice.

266
00:11:38,250 --> 00:11:39,070
Kit.

267
00:11:39,570 --> 00:11:41,050
She didn't repeat it out loud.

268
00:11:41,430 --> 00:11:42,250
She kept it.

269
00:11:42,430 --> 00:11:43,850
She was very good at that.

270
00:11:44,110 --> 00:11:45,630
That night Roena didn't sleep.

271
00:11:46,010 --> 00:11:47,790
She lay looking at the bedroom ceiling,

272
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:50,190
listening to his breathing beside her.

273
00:11:50,390 --> 00:11:52,630
That breathing she knew better than her own,

274
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:54,750
that she could tell when it was real sleep,

275
00:11:55,010 --> 00:11:55,970
and when it was faked.

276
00:11:56,510 --> 00:11:58,910
That night for the first time she couldn't read it.

277
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:02,650
Outside, the river ran with its usual soft sound,

278
00:12:03,330 --> 00:12:06,130
indifferent to what was happening inside that beautiful house.

279
00:12:06,130 --> 00:12:09,730
Inside her chest, an empty chair had begun to creak.

280
00:12:10,670 --> 00:12:11,410
The second.

281
00:12:11,410 --> 00:12:13,390
Chapter two, tenderness isn't truth.

282
00:12:14,870 --> 00:12:17,550
Sun came into the bedroom in the morning, as if nothing had happened,

283
00:12:18,070 --> 00:12:20,550
and Jago moved in bed the way he always did.

284
00:12:20,770 --> 00:12:23,050
His hand seeking her waist beneath the sheet,

285
00:12:23,550 --> 00:12:25,690
his face pressing into the nape of her neck,

286
00:12:26,150 --> 00:12:28,810
the short kiss at the spot where her hair began.

287
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:31,530
Roena lay still, eyes closed,

288
00:12:32,010 --> 00:12:33,570
and received it all with her skin.

289
00:12:33,990 --> 00:12:35,230
His warmth was real.

290
00:12:35,230 --> 00:12:37,310
The weight of his arm was real.

291
00:12:37,690 --> 00:12:40,090
It was easier to stay quiet a second longer,

292
00:12:40,490 --> 00:12:43,750
and let her body believe in what her mind hadn't yet resolved.

293
00:12:44,330 --> 00:12:45,510
Then she turned over.

294
00:12:45,810 --> 00:12:46,290
Jago.

295
00:12:47,290 --> 00:12:48,110
The call yesterday.

296
00:12:48,610 --> 00:12:50,930
He opened his eyes with a staged laziness.

297
00:12:51,450 --> 00:12:52,310
She saw the staging.

298
00:12:52,830 --> 00:12:55,950
It was quick, almost imperceptible, but she saw it.

299
00:12:56,150 --> 00:12:59,850
She'd learn to see the small things in him before she'd learn their names.

300
00:13:00,290 --> 00:13:02,270
I already told you my love, it was nobody.

301
00:13:02,270 --> 00:13:03,590
You went white.

302
00:13:04,050 --> 00:13:05,930
Jago smiled with half his mouth,

303
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:10,410
that small smile he reserved for diffusing difficult situations in boardrooms.

304
00:13:10,790 --> 00:13:13,830
He raised his hand and tucked a strand of her hair behind her ear,

305
00:13:14,230 --> 00:13:15,890
with a calculated lightness.

306
00:13:16,290 --> 00:13:18,170
A gesture that had always worked before.

307
00:13:18,630 --> 00:13:21,070
One she herself had loved in those first months,

308
00:13:21,490 --> 00:13:23,430
when she still couldn't tell genuine tenderness

309
00:13:23,430 --> 00:13:25,710
from the tenderness that served as a curtain.

310
00:13:26,090 --> 00:13:29,110
I didn't, he said, his voice low and firm,

311
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:30,770
you were against the light.

312
00:13:30,770 --> 00:13:32,490
She looked at him in silence.

313
00:13:33,110 --> 00:13:34,890
A pause of three, four seconds,

314
00:13:35,430 --> 00:13:38,530
enough for any guilty person to fill the emptiness with more words.

315
00:13:38,810 --> 00:13:40,670
He didn't fill it, he was too good for that.

316
00:13:40,950 --> 00:13:43,990
He leaned in, kissed the corner of her mouth with a tenderness

317
00:13:43,990 --> 00:13:46,790
that was real and at the same time evasive about everything,

318
00:13:47,310 --> 00:13:48,710
and spoke against her skin.

319
00:13:49,130 --> 00:13:49,970
Let's have coffee.

320
00:13:50,610 --> 00:13:51,510
Rowena let it go.

321
00:13:51,950 --> 00:13:52,850
She kissed him back.

322
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:55,770
Short, got up, went to shower alone.

323
00:13:56,270 --> 00:13:58,410
And while the water fell too hot on her shoulders,

324
00:13:58,410 --> 00:14:01,390
she thought for the first time in plain terms,

325
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:03,650
a sentence that bothered her a great deal.

326
00:14:04,210 --> 00:14:07,110
Tenderness and truth are not the same thing.

327
00:14:07,370 --> 00:14:09,950
She stayed under the water longer than she needed to.

328
00:14:10,230 --> 00:14:12,110
The bathroom smelled of the citrus soap

329
00:14:12,110 --> 00:14:15,590
Jago had started buying for her when he noticed which one she liked.

330
00:14:16,150 --> 00:14:17,550
One more detail he memorized,

331
00:14:18,230 --> 00:14:20,870
one more gesture she no longer knew how to receive.

332
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:23,090
She came down dressed to go out.

333
00:14:23,390 --> 00:14:25,470
Linen pants, a light-colored blouse.

334
00:14:25,970 --> 00:14:27,890
A small bag she used when she went downtown.

335
00:14:27,890 --> 00:14:30,810
Jago was in the kitchen reading something on the tablet

336
00:14:30,810 --> 00:14:34,890
with a cup of coffee in front of him that must have been half-loop warm by now.

337
00:14:35,190 --> 00:14:38,530
He looked at her with that gaze that crossed the room without needing distance.

338
00:14:39,050 --> 00:14:39,790
Where are you going?

339
00:14:40,230 --> 00:14:42,490
She founded amusing, not the question.

340
00:14:43,050 --> 00:14:43,590
The tone.

341
00:14:44,150 --> 00:14:45,210
It was his old tone.

342
00:14:45,650 --> 00:14:49,130
The one she thought had been left behind since they'd gotten themselves organized.

343
00:14:49,730 --> 00:14:52,150
Six months earlier to live together there near the river.

344
00:14:52,810 --> 00:14:54,510
Downtown, by a couple things.

345
00:14:55,110 --> 00:14:56,490
Marlo arrives today, remember?

346
00:14:56,490 --> 00:14:57,630
I remember.

347
00:14:58,190 --> 00:14:59,090
He set down the tablet.

348
00:14:59,690 --> 00:15:00,450
Taking the car?

349
00:15:00,930 --> 00:15:02,010
I'm driving myself.

350
00:15:02,470 --> 00:15:04,370
He nodded as if he were accepting it.

351
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:05,410
He reached out.

352
00:15:05,670 --> 00:15:07,550
Took a hand on the cold marble counter,

353
00:15:08,210 --> 00:15:08,930
squeezed it lightly.

354
00:15:09,430 --> 00:15:14,130
His fingers wrapping around hers with the ease of someone who already knew every knuckle.

355
00:15:14,630 --> 00:15:15,010
Be careful.

356
00:15:16,490 --> 00:15:17,690
She went out the side door.

357
00:15:18,130 --> 00:15:20,230
She walked along the stone hallway to the garage,

358
00:15:20,650 --> 00:15:21,990
took the keys off the hook.

359
00:15:22,450 --> 00:15:24,690
The air outside smelled of the river's dampness

360
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:27,790
and of some neighbouring garden that must have had Jasmine.

361
00:15:28,350 --> 00:15:31,410
It was early enough that Savannah's heat hadn't yet weighed down.

362
00:15:31,730 --> 00:15:33,270
When she opened the electric gate,

363
00:15:33,690 --> 00:15:37,510
two men in suits were standing outside next to a dark car she didn't recognize.

364
00:15:38,110 --> 00:15:39,430
They didn't seem like a threat.

365
00:15:39,830 --> 00:15:40,810
They seemed like scenery.

366
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:44,010
The scenery of another kind of house, not hers.

367
00:15:44,570 --> 00:15:46,930
One of them approached with a smile that was too polite.

368
00:15:47,490 --> 00:15:49,670
Mrs. Pike, good morning, will be going with you.

369
00:15:49,890 --> 00:15:50,810
Rowena blinked.

370
00:15:51,130 --> 00:15:52,210
Going with me, where?

371
00:15:52,590 --> 00:15:53,430
Wherever you go.

372
00:15:53,430 --> 00:15:54,290
House orders.

373
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:55,130
Security.

374
00:15:55,770 --> 00:15:56,830
She looked at the man.

375
00:15:57,110 --> 00:15:58,130
Looked at the other one.

376
00:15:58,510 --> 00:15:59,850
Neither of them seemed embarrassed.

377
00:16:00,470 --> 00:16:02,510
Neither of them seemed to expect her to argue.

378
00:16:03,070 --> 00:16:05,470
That, more than anything else, was what bothered her,

379
00:16:05,690 --> 00:16:09,510
that they derived ready for the normalcy of a situation she hadn't authorized.

380
00:16:10,050 --> 00:16:11,390
I didn't ask for security.

381
00:16:11,930 --> 00:16:14,510
She said, with a calm that wasn't easy to maintain.

382
00:16:15,050 --> 00:16:17,570
You don't need to ask, Mom, it's already been arranged.

383
00:16:18,070 --> 00:16:20,070
She stood for a second on the stone pavement.

384
00:16:20,070 --> 00:16:23,690
Inside the house, behind her, Jago knew.

385
00:16:24,130 --> 00:16:26,950
Jago was on the tablet with the lukewarm cup and he knew.

386
00:16:27,250 --> 00:16:29,990
He'd given the order the day before at the downtown office.

387
00:16:30,430 --> 00:16:33,570
And he knew the exact second she'd meet those two men at the gate.

388
00:16:34,010 --> 00:16:36,430
At that very moment, sitting in the kitchen,

389
00:16:36,870 --> 00:16:40,150
he swallowed some coffee that was too cold to cover his own nerves.

390
00:16:40,710 --> 00:16:43,870
His hand pressing lightly on the tablet for no reason at all.

391
00:16:44,170 --> 00:16:45,510
Rowena didn't make a scene.

392
00:16:45,790 --> 00:16:48,990
She simply said, all right, she got into her car.

393
00:16:48,990 --> 00:16:50,830
Let their car follow behind.

394
00:16:51,330 --> 00:16:54,030
She drove to downtown Savannah with both hands on the wheel

395
00:16:54,030 --> 00:16:58,350
and the silence inside the car so vast that she turned on the radio.

396
00:16:58,950 --> 00:17:00,110
Found it unbearable.

397
00:17:00,590 --> 00:17:01,310
Turned it off.

398
00:17:01,730 --> 00:17:03,570
A hand stayed on the leather of the wheel,

399
00:17:03,970 --> 00:17:07,470
and she looked out the window at the old Magnolia's lining the avenue.

400
00:17:08,150 --> 00:17:09,850
White and heavy from so much blooming

401
00:17:09,850 --> 00:17:13,310
and thought that some beautiful things were also suffocating.

402
00:17:13,770 --> 00:17:17,190
Marlo Trent showed up on time at the old cafe in the historic district,

403
00:17:17,190 --> 00:17:20,630
with a bag too big for anything she could possibly need there.

404
00:17:20,910 --> 00:17:23,690
And an expression Rowena recognized from far off.

405
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:26,350
The expression of someone who'd flown three hours

406
00:17:26,350 --> 00:17:29,690
to give a dose of reality to someone she loved very much

407
00:17:29,690 --> 00:17:31,470
and who was in need of hearing it.

408
00:17:31,870 --> 00:17:35,230
Row, Marlo, they hugged the way they'd hugged for years,

409
00:17:35,570 --> 00:17:36,490
tight without ceremony.

410
00:17:37,230 --> 00:17:41,590
Marlo rubbing her hand twice on her back with that energy of someone who'd arrived to fix something.

411
00:17:42,030 --> 00:17:45,830
The cafe smelled of cinnamon and burnt coffee from an old machine,

412
00:17:45,830 --> 00:17:49,170
and the dark wooden tables had marks from years of cups.

413
00:17:49,630 --> 00:17:50,590
They sat near the window.

414
00:17:51,230 --> 00:17:52,370
Marlo ordered black coffee.

415
00:17:52,970 --> 00:17:54,110
Rowena, a cappuccino.

416
00:17:54,750 --> 00:17:57,550
Across the street the dark car parked with professional discretion.

417
00:17:58,150 --> 00:18:02,150
Those two yours, Marlo pointed with her chin, no filter at all.

418
00:18:02,590 --> 00:18:04,450
They're the houses, the houses.

419
00:18:05,150 --> 00:18:07,050
Yeah, Marlo raised a eyebrow.

420
00:18:07,630 --> 00:18:11,730
Marlo had an eyebrow that asked whole questions on its own without needing anything more.

421
00:18:11,730 --> 00:18:13,590
Row, don't start.

422
00:18:14,210 --> 00:18:16,230
Row, love doesn't treat you like a hostage.

423
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:17,570
Rowena loved.

424
00:18:18,090 --> 00:18:20,350
It was a short laugh a little awkward but honest.

425
00:18:20,830 --> 00:18:22,630
And she felt along with it a good pang.

426
00:18:23,150 --> 00:18:27,990
The pang of someone being reminded of herself by someone who'd known her before all of this.

427
00:18:28,250 --> 00:18:29,450
They talked for an hour.

428
00:18:29,910 --> 00:18:34,350
Marlo talked about the newsroom about the new editor who'd reorganized everything.

429
00:18:34,810 --> 00:18:39,910
About the people who still asked about Rowena now and then with that mix of curiosity and respect

430
00:18:39,910 --> 00:18:41,930
that comes just before being forgotten.

431
00:18:42,490 --> 00:18:45,250
Rowena listened and wanted to feel a clean kind of longing,

432
00:18:45,950 --> 00:18:49,310
uncomplicated, but the longing that arrived had an uneven edge.

433
00:18:49,750 --> 00:18:53,850
At some point, out of old reflex, she took the recorder from her bag.

434
00:18:54,270 --> 00:18:58,610
A small, silver recorder that she carried out of a habit of more than six years,

435
00:18:58,910 --> 00:19:00,230
always in the side pocket.

436
00:19:00,670 --> 00:19:05,590
She looked at the device in the palm of her hand as if she weren't sure when it had ended up there.

437
00:19:05,830 --> 00:19:08,230
She put it back without pressing a single button.

438
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:09,570
Marlo saw it.

439
00:19:09,570 --> 00:19:12,110
Marlo saw everything always had.

440
00:19:12,370 --> 00:19:13,630
Who are you now journalist?

441
00:19:14,170 --> 00:19:18,530
She asked, with the corner of her mouth croaked in a way that was both a question and affection.

442
00:19:19,230 --> 00:19:20,870
Rowena laughed for real this time.

443
00:19:21,310 --> 00:19:23,390
A bigger laugh that arrived without warning.

444
00:19:24,010 --> 00:19:26,730
A woman waiting for an answer that never comes.

445
00:19:27,230 --> 00:19:27,770
What answer?

446
00:19:28,310 --> 00:19:28,830
A proposal?

447
00:19:29,510 --> 00:19:30,090
A job offer?

448
00:19:30,530 --> 00:19:31,610
They sent it last week.

449
00:19:32,090 --> 00:19:33,470
I still haven't gotten any reply.

450
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:35,570
Marlo kept looking at her.

451
00:19:35,570 --> 00:19:39,350
She held the cup with both hands and waited a second longer before speaking.

452
00:19:39,790 --> 00:19:41,110
That second rowing a new.

453
00:19:41,610 --> 00:19:44,430
The second that came before the sentences that stayed.

454
00:19:44,970 --> 00:19:45,130
Row.

455
00:19:45,730 --> 00:19:45,970
What?

456
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:47,870
Are you sure it didn't come?

457
00:19:48,310 --> 00:19:50,150
Rowena stopped the cappuccino midway.

458
00:19:50,570 --> 00:19:51,730
The cup hung suspended.

459
00:19:52,370 --> 00:19:54,050
The heat rising to her face.

460
00:19:54,530 --> 00:19:55,310
What do you mean?

461
00:19:55,790 --> 00:19:56,190
Nothing.

462
00:19:56,790 --> 00:19:57,810
Marlo deflected.

463
00:19:58,070 --> 00:20:02,230
And looked at the dark car across the street with an expression that was nothing.

464
00:20:02,750 --> 00:20:03,450
Never mind.

465
00:20:03,830 --> 00:20:04,890
But the sentence stayed.

466
00:20:04,890 --> 00:20:08,450
Marlo knew how to put sentences in the air the way they'd hang suspended.

467
00:20:08,990 --> 00:20:10,650
And this one stayed the rest of the coffee.

468
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:12,250
The rest of the way back.

469
00:20:12,470 --> 00:20:13,610
The rest of the whole afternoon.

470
00:20:14,410 --> 00:20:17,210
Rowena returned to the house near the river in the late afternoon.

471
00:20:17,710 --> 00:20:21,070
With savanna's golden light striking the paving stones from the side.

472
00:20:21,510 --> 00:20:26,170
And a thin mist rising from the river as it always did when the heat began to give way.

473
00:20:26,630 --> 00:20:29,410
The two men followed behind in professional silence.

474
00:20:30,010 --> 00:20:31,890
Jego was still at the downtown office.

475
00:20:32,310 --> 00:20:33,370
The house was quiet.

476
00:20:33,370 --> 00:20:35,150
Only neither in the kitchen.

477
00:20:35,670 --> 00:20:38,190
Cutting something with that silent precision of hers.

478
00:20:38,630 --> 00:20:43,030
And the smell of rosemary coming from some pot that had been on the stove for a while.

479
00:20:43,450 --> 00:20:49,010
Rowena went into Jego's private study with an excuse she'd prepared for herself while still in the car.

480
00:20:49,450 --> 00:20:52,250
She needed that old contract from the house renovation work.

481
00:20:52,590 --> 00:20:55,470
The carpenter had asked for a copy of the original specification.

482
00:20:56,090 --> 00:20:57,250
It was a polite lie.

483
00:20:57,590 --> 00:21:00,530
The kind you tell yourself before doing what you were going to do anyway.

484
00:21:00,530 --> 00:21:02,210
She opened the first drawer.

485
00:21:02,730 --> 00:21:09,250
Office papers all in order labeled with the precision of a man who tolerated chaos on no surface.

486
00:21:10,050 --> 00:21:10,590
Second drawer.

487
00:21:11,170 --> 00:21:11,810
Contracts.

488
00:21:12,090 --> 00:21:13,930
Thin folders with dates and numbers.

489
00:21:14,510 --> 00:21:15,230
Third drawer.

490
00:21:15,710 --> 00:21:16,650
A cream-coloured envelope.

491
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:18,150
No return address.

492
00:21:18,670 --> 00:21:21,110
With her name in the center in the impersonal.

493
00:21:21,290 --> 00:21:22,190
Typewritten handwriting.

494
00:21:22,870 --> 00:21:24,710
Let her head in the upper right corner.

495
00:21:25,230 --> 00:21:27,410
Winslow foundation for independent journalism.

496
00:21:27,910 --> 00:21:29,170
The envelope was open.

497
00:21:29,510 --> 00:21:30,430
She stood still.

498
00:21:30,850 --> 00:21:33,010
The study itself went still around her.

499
00:21:33,170 --> 00:21:36,210
The dark shelves, the books lined up by size.

500
00:21:36,670 --> 00:21:40,730
The narrow window that looked out onto the side garden with the moss on the stones.

501
00:21:41,270 --> 00:21:43,090
Her hands went strangely quiet.

502
00:21:43,470 --> 00:21:44,390
She took the envelope.

503
00:21:44,810 --> 00:21:49,810
She pulled out the contents carefully, as if the paper might confirm something she already knew.

504
00:21:50,110 --> 00:21:51,430
But didn't yet want to name.

505
00:21:51,930 --> 00:21:52,670
Two sheets.

506
00:21:53,210 --> 00:21:54,710
The first was the formal invitation.

507
00:21:55,390 --> 00:21:56,090
A job offer.

508
00:21:56,090 --> 00:22:00,850
A series of long investigative reports full ground complete autonomy over the topics.

509
00:22:01,350 --> 00:22:03,970
An offer that would bring her career back to life from scratch.

510
00:22:04,450 --> 00:22:06,830
At the exact point where she'd left off before Savannah.

511
00:22:07,510 --> 00:22:08,230
Before the ball.

512
00:22:08,690 --> 00:22:09,370
Before everything.

513
00:22:10,050 --> 00:22:11,990
The second sheet was a carbon copy.

514
00:22:12,470 --> 00:22:13,050
A reply.

515
00:22:13,630 --> 00:22:15,030
Dated 10 days ago.

516
00:22:15,470 --> 00:22:16,210
Dear Serz.

517
00:22:16,730 --> 00:22:18,550
We thank you for your generous consideration.

518
00:22:19,270 --> 00:22:23,130
At this time Miss Pike is not available to take on new professional commitments.

519
00:22:23,130 --> 00:22:24,870
We renew our thanks.

520
00:22:25,430 --> 00:22:27,390
A signature at the bottom in handwriting.

521
00:22:28,030 --> 00:22:31,370
The same handwriting that appeared in the notes he left her in the kitchen in the morning.

522
00:22:31,970 --> 00:22:34,610
The same as the contract she signed alongside him.

523
00:22:34,850 --> 00:22:38,590
The same one she'd learned to recognize before even reading what was written.

524
00:22:39,070 --> 00:22:39,910
Is handwriting.

525
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:43,530
Ruinna kept looking at the sheet for a length of time she couldn't measure.

526
00:22:44,070 --> 00:22:45,170
Her body didn't tremble.

527
00:22:45,570 --> 00:22:47,050
Her body went very still.

528
00:22:47,430 --> 00:22:49,830
And the stillness was heavier than any tremor.

529
00:22:50,270 --> 00:22:52,030
Ruinna put the envelope back in the drawer.

530
00:22:52,030 --> 00:22:54,750
Closed it with the same care she'd opened it.

531
00:22:54,910 --> 00:22:57,910
She left the private study without taking the carpenters contract.

532
00:22:58,290 --> 00:22:59,570
She didn't need the contract.

533
00:22:59,950 --> 00:23:00,770
She never had.

534
00:23:01,130 --> 00:23:02,250
She went to the living room.

535
00:23:02,630 --> 00:23:05,250
She sat on the sofa without turning on the light.

536
00:23:05,710 --> 00:23:10,230
The afternoon had closed into that dark blue of early night that came fast in Savannah's summer.

537
00:23:10,710 --> 00:23:12,650
And the room filled with a warm dimness.

538
00:23:13,070 --> 00:23:14,770
On the other side next to the big window.

539
00:23:15,290 --> 00:23:17,270
The empty chair was in its usual place.

540
00:23:17,630 --> 00:23:20,090
With the last light of day reaching only the backrest.

541
00:23:20,090 --> 00:23:22,670
She looked at the chair for a long time.

542
00:23:23,050 --> 00:23:24,790
Two stories she thought.

543
00:23:25,290 --> 00:23:28,950
One of them has a short old name that no one pronounces inside this house.

544
00:23:29,290 --> 00:23:33,310
The other has his handwriting on a sheet that answered for her without her knowing.

545
00:23:33,850 --> 00:23:34,570
The phone rang.

546
00:23:34,970 --> 00:23:35,770
It was Jago.

547
00:23:36,350 --> 00:23:36,570
Love.

548
00:23:37,130 --> 00:23:38,510
I'm not going to make it home yet.

549
00:23:38,950 --> 00:23:39,770
Don't stay hungry.

550
00:23:40,330 --> 00:23:41,450
Eat without me.

551
00:23:41,730 --> 00:23:42,670
She closed her eyes.

552
00:23:43,110 --> 00:23:44,890
She held her voice in the right place.

553
00:23:45,210 --> 00:23:49,530
That exact place where the voice stops trembling and becomes just an answer.

554
00:23:49,530 --> 00:23:50,370
Okay.

555
00:23:50,850 --> 00:23:51,670
I love you.

556
00:23:51,930 --> 00:23:52,570
You too.

557
00:23:52,870 --> 00:23:53,570
She hung up.

558
00:23:53,750 --> 00:23:55,150
She kept the phone in her hand.

559
00:23:55,610 --> 00:23:57,450
The heat of the device against her palm.

560
00:23:57,990 --> 00:24:01,950
Outside the river ran with that low constant sound she'd learned to find calming

561
00:24:01,950 --> 00:24:03,610
and that now sounded different.

562
00:24:04,090 --> 00:24:05,330
The empty chair waited.

563
00:24:05,930 --> 00:24:07,790
And for the first time in six months,

564
00:24:08,150 --> 00:24:10,110
Rowena Pike felt inside her own chest.

565
00:24:10,570 --> 00:24:13,410
The low firm creek of a decision beginning to be made.

566
00:24:15,230 --> 00:24:17,150
Chapter 3 The Name No One Said.

567
00:24:18,130 --> 00:24:20,870
The cream envelope sat on the table between them

568
00:24:20,870 --> 00:24:23,350
as if it weighed more than the wood holding it up.

569
00:24:23,750 --> 00:24:25,930
Rowena had waited all day to set it down there

570
00:24:25,930 --> 00:24:28,530
at the exact spot where he usually left his keys.

571
00:24:28,990 --> 00:24:33,450
She chose the dining room table because it was the only room where Jago couldn't lean on a

572
00:24:33,450 --> 00:24:34,010
work object.

573
00:24:34,490 --> 00:24:36,570
No paper, no pen, no phone.

574
00:24:36,930 --> 00:24:40,130
Just him, her and his handwriting betraying his handwriting.

575
00:24:40,810 --> 00:24:42,190
Jago came in after eight.

576
00:24:42,470 --> 00:24:46,150
He took off his jacket with the slowness of someone who already knew what he'd find.

577
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:49,850
The house near the Savannah River smelled of jasmine from the garden outside.

578
00:24:50,330 --> 00:24:55,750
An out of season sweetness that only worsened the sensation that the air was breathing on its own.

579
00:24:55,970 --> 00:24:56,890
He saw the envelope.

580
00:24:57,350 --> 00:24:58,690
He didn't ask what it was.

581
00:24:59,070 --> 00:25:02,310
Inside he felt a lying sentence form before he could stop it.

582
00:25:02,510 --> 00:25:04,770
I was going to tell you and in the same instant,

583
00:25:05,170 --> 00:25:06,210
new it was false.

584
00:25:06,570 --> 00:25:07,610
He wasn't going to.

585
00:25:07,770 --> 00:25:11,570
If she hadn't found it, that paper would have died at the bottom of that drawer.

586
00:25:12,050 --> 00:25:15,050
Rowena, his voice came out too controlled to be sincere.

587
00:25:15,050 --> 00:25:16,910
It's not what it looks like.

588
00:25:17,150 --> 00:25:19,190
She crossed her arms over her linen dress.

589
00:25:19,570 --> 00:25:20,350
She didn't sit.

590
00:25:20,670 --> 00:25:23,650
The yellow light of the chandelier fell between them like a border.

591
00:25:24,130 --> 00:25:25,950
It's exactly what it looks like Jago.

592
00:25:26,430 --> 00:25:27,470
He breathed in deep.

593
00:25:27,910 --> 00:25:30,450
The cold panic settled between one river and another.

594
00:25:30,830 --> 00:25:34,170
That old cold he knew from another night, 10 years ago.

595
00:25:34,410 --> 00:25:36,530
He swallowed twice before he managed to speak.

596
00:25:36,970 --> 00:25:38,410
I wanted to protect you.

597
00:25:38,630 --> 00:25:39,510
From a job offer.

598
00:25:39,890 --> 00:25:43,170
From an offer that was going to take you away from Savannah for six months.

599
00:25:43,170 --> 00:25:45,210
Rowena smiled without joy.

600
00:25:45,690 --> 00:25:48,250
And the decision to go or stay was yours.

601
00:25:48,710 --> 00:25:50,510
He opened his mouth and found no answer.

602
00:25:50,950 --> 00:25:53,650
She continued lower because the low voice hurt more.

603
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:54,990
You answered for me.

604
00:25:55,050 --> 00:25:56,710
You said, thank you for me.

605
00:25:56,890 --> 00:25:58,110
You declined for me.

606
00:25:58,510 --> 00:26:01,570
Each sentence fell like a small stone into the bottom of a glass.

607
00:26:02,030 --> 00:26:03,270
And then you brought me breakfast.

608
00:26:03,910 --> 00:26:04,190
Rowena.

609
00:26:04,870 --> 00:26:05,090
No.

610
00:26:05,590 --> 00:26:06,590
She raised her hand.

611
00:26:07,010 --> 00:26:09,250
And her hand was trembling and she hated that.

612
00:26:09,490 --> 00:26:11,110
You're not going to ask me for time.

613
00:26:11,110 --> 00:26:13,970
Time is the one thing you shouldn't ask for today.

614
00:26:14,390 --> 00:26:15,610
You had six months.

615
00:26:15,970 --> 00:26:17,390
He took a step toward her.

616
00:26:17,630 --> 00:26:18,790
She took a step back.

617
00:26:19,050 --> 00:26:20,110
It was a small movement.

618
00:26:20,630 --> 00:26:23,950
But he felt as if he'd been shoved against the opposite wall of the room.

619
00:26:24,470 --> 00:26:26,050
Inside something in him.

620
00:26:26,310 --> 00:26:29,370
The part that was always certain began to crack.

621
00:26:29,790 --> 00:26:33,710
He watched her mouth pronounce the next sentence before he heard it.

622
00:26:33,830 --> 00:26:34,590
Who is Kit?

623
00:26:35,030 --> 00:26:38,270
The name fell to the dining room floor and stayed there gleaming.

624
00:26:38,750 --> 00:26:40,030
Jago looked at the envelope.

625
00:26:40,030 --> 00:26:41,430
Looked at her.

626
00:26:41,590 --> 00:26:44,370
Looked at the window that faced the dark river outside.

627
00:26:44,910 --> 00:26:45,610
He said nothing.

628
00:26:46,150 --> 00:26:48,690
And his silence was the first real confession.

629
00:26:49,370 --> 00:26:50,070
Good night, Jago.

630
00:26:50,590 --> 00:26:51,950
She went up the stairs slowly.

631
00:26:52,530 --> 00:26:57,090
He stood beside the table for too long listening to her footsteps disappear into the upstairs hallway.

632
00:26:57,610 --> 00:27:02,110
Then he sat in the nearest chair elbows on his knees and stared at his own envelope as if

633
00:27:02,110 --> 00:27:04,370
the paper were capable of answering for him.

634
00:27:04,730 --> 00:27:05,770
Rowena didn't sleep.

635
00:27:06,110 --> 00:27:09,510
She spent the small hours with her eyes open at the ceiling of the guest room.

636
00:27:09,510 --> 00:27:13,990
That room she'd never entered before and where the sheets smelled of forgotten lavender.

637
00:27:14,430 --> 00:27:17,070
She mentally repeated the list of things she knew.

638
00:27:17,410 --> 00:27:19,370
The name, the chair, the terrace.

639
00:27:19,970 --> 00:27:22,590
Udora's remark about a laugh that wasn't hers.

640
00:27:23,050 --> 00:27:24,790
The payments she hadn't yet traced.

641
00:27:25,230 --> 00:27:26,850
The envelope answered in his handwriting.

642
00:27:27,530 --> 00:27:29,050
There were two stories being hidden.

643
00:27:29,430 --> 00:27:31,010
She needed to unravel both.

644
00:27:31,450 --> 00:27:35,230
In the morning before the sun rose fully, she called a taxi from the street.

645
00:27:35,570 --> 00:27:37,070
She didn't ask for a house car.

646
00:27:37,410 --> 00:27:38,430
She didn't tell Fielen.

647
00:27:38,430 --> 00:27:43,650
She put on the plainest clothes she had and went out the side door and no guard saw her,

648
00:27:43,870 --> 00:27:46,790
because no guard expected her to leave before six in the morning.

649
00:27:47,390 --> 00:27:52,030
Silas Ashford's office was in downtown Savannah in an old townhouse with tall windows

650
00:27:52,030 --> 00:27:54,710
and a permanent smell of coffee and old paper.

651
00:27:55,190 --> 00:27:58,130
The sun hadn't yet warm the sidewalk when she climbed the steps.

652
00:27:58,670 --> 00:28:00,270
Silas answered the door himself.

653
00:28:00,670 --> 00:28:02,010
He didn't even ask what she wanted.

654
00:28:02,390 --> 00:28:04,550
He just pointed to the chair in front of the desk.

655
00:28:04,970 --> 00:28:06,590
You already know why I'm here.

656
00:28:06,590 --> 00:28:08,250
I'm pretty sure I do.

657
00:28:08,570 --> 00:28:10,410
Silas poured two coffees without asking.

658
00:28:10,990 --> 00:28:13,010
And I'm pretty sure I shouldn't open my mouth.

659
00:28:13,550 --> 00:28:16,270
Roeena accepted the coffee and didn't drink it.

660
00:28:16,610 --> 00:28:16,970
Silas.

661
00:28:17,530 --> 00:28:19,550
Her voice came out firmer than she expected.

662
00:28:20,130 --> 00:28:21,690
Your his friend, I know that.

663
00:28:22,050 --> 00:28:25,170
But you were also the only one who looked me in the eye that night at the ball

664
00:28:25,170 --> 00:28:27,630
and didn't pretend not to see what you were seeing.

665
00:28:28,010 --> 00:28:29,710
I need to know who kit is.

666
00:28:30,070 --> 00:28:32,290
Silas let the coffee rest between his hands.

667
00:28:32,770 --> 00:28:34,470
He stared at the tabletop for long enough

668
00:28:34,470 --> 00:28:37,710
that Roeena understood the answer would hurt him too.

669
00:28:38,010 --> 00:28:38,950
Kit was his brother.

670
00:28:39,370 --> 00:28:40,010
He said it last.

671
00:28:40,550 --> 00:28:40,890
Younger.

672
00:28:41,410 --> 00:28:41,650
Was.

673
00:28:42,210 --> 00:28:43,690
That's what they say in Savannah.

674
00:28:44,330 --> 00:28:45,290
And what do you say?

675
00:28:45,790 --> 00:28:46,910
Silas raised his eyes.

676
00:28:47,330 --> 00:28:48,750
There was a new caution in them.

677
00:28:49,030 --> 00:28:51,930
The caution of someone crossing a line and knowing it.

678
00:28:52,110 --> 00:28:54,590
I say there was a boating accident 10 years ago

679
00:28:54,590 --> 00:28:56,490
that the boat was found destroyed.

680
00:28:57,030 --> 00:28:59,070
That the family buried a closed casket.

681
00:28:59,590 --> 00:29:00,070
He paused.

682
00:29:00,530 --> 00:29:02,370
And that Jego never believed it.

683
00:29:02,370 --> 00:29:04,270
Roeena felt her own chest drop.

684
00:29:04,630 --> 00:29:06,310
Why did he never believe it?

685
00:29:06,610 --> 00:29:07,930
Silas shook his head slowly.

686
00:29:08,570 --> 00:29:08,930
Roeena.

687
00:29:09,410 --> 00:29:09,890
Not today.

688
00:29:10,310 --> 00:29:10,850
Not this.

689
00:29:11,330 --> 00:29:12,690
This isn't mine to tell.

690
00:29:13,330 --> 00:29:13,670
Silas.

691
00:29:14,170 --> 00:29:15,770
I've already said more than I should.

692
00:29:16,230 --> 00:29:17,110
He looked at the door.

693
00:29:17,390 --> 00:29:18,590
Go home ask him.

694
00:29:18,870 --> 00:29:19,810
He won't answer me.

695
00:29:20,070 --> 00:29:21,730
Then come back here when he doesn't.

696
00:29:22,070 --> 00:29:22,770
She got up.

697
00:29:22,990 --> 00:29:24,070
At the door she stopped.

698
00:29:24,530 --> 00:29:26,310
She didn't look back when she said.

699
00:29:26,530 --> 00:29:27,110
Thank you.

700
00:29:27,490 --> 00:29:28,450
Silas didn't answer.

701
00:29:28,930 --> 00:29:31,250
He kept looking at her coffee that hadn't been drunk.

702
00:29:31,250 --> 00:29:33,370
And for the first time in 10 years,

703
00:29:33,750 --> 00:29:35,950
he felt he might be betraying the right friend.

704
00:29:36,370 --> 00:29:37,710
Back at the house near the river.

705
00:29:38,230 --> 00:29:39,770
Roeena found Neve in the kitchen,

706
00:29:40,290 --> 00:29:42,670
arranging sprigs of basil in a glass jar.

707
00:29:43,070 --> 00:29:45,950
The old housekeeper had her hair pinned up in a loose bun

708
00:29:45,950 --> 00:29:48,250
and wore the same grey apron as always.

709
00:29:48,770 --> 00:29:51,650
Roeena stopped in the doorway for a second before going in.

710
00:29:52,010 --> 00:29:55,470
Neve belonged to that house more than Jego belonged to it.

711
00:29:55,590 --> 00:29:57,590
If anyone knew, it was her.

712
00:29:57,970 --> 00:29:58,310
Neve.

713
00:29:58,770 --> 00:29:59,650
The woman looked up.

714
00:29:59,650 --> 00:30:02,390
She smiled with that small smile she kept for Roeena.

715
00:30:02,950 --> 00:30:03,770
Good morning dear.

716
00:30:04,170 --> 00:30:05,210
Shall I make some tea?

717
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:05,930
Neve.

718
00:30:06,410 --> 00:30:06,890
Who is kid?

719
00:30:07,390 --> 00:30:11,190
The smile disappeared so fast that Roeena almost doubted it had existed.

720
00:30:11,870 --> 00:30:13,810
Neve's hands gripped the jar too hard.

721
00:30:14,330 --> 00:30:16,390
One of the sprigs slipped and fell into the sink.

722
00:30:16,950 --> 00:30:17,290
Oh dear.

723
00:30:17,830 --> 00:30:18,170
Please.

724
00:30:18,770 --> 00:30:20,670
Neve looked at the door leading to the hallway.

725
00:30:21,110 --> 00:30:23,050
She looked at the window that faced the garden,

726
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:25,530
where the morning Jasmine was still closed.

727
00:30:25,890 --> 00:30:29,010
She looked at the counter as if the answer might be printed on the marble.

728
00:30:29,010 --> 00:30:30,570
It's not my place.

729
00:30:30,950 --> 00:30:31,930
I know it isn't.

730
00:30:32,190 --> 00:30:33,450
Roeena took a step closer,

731
00:30:33,990 --> 00:30:36,130
but I've been sleeping in this house for six months.

732
00:30:36,590 --> 00:30:38,830
And I can't pretend anymore that I don't see.

733
00:30:39,290 --> 00:30:40,430
He avoids the terrace.

734
00:30:40,990 --> 00:30:41,910
You avoid answering.

735
00:30:42,550 --> 00:30:44,990
Mrs. Udora has never said that name near me.

736
00:30:45,370 --> 00:30:46,910
And last night I asked my husband,

737
00:30:47,450 --> 00:30:49,790
the word slipped out before she could choose another.

738
00:30:50,130 --> 00:30:51,190
And he went silent.

739
00:30:51,790 --> 00:30:53,170
Neve closed her eyes.

740
00:30:53,510 --> 00:30:54,650
He avoids the terrace.

741
00:30:55,190 --> 00:30:57,230
The voice came out broken almost inaudible,

742
00:30:57,230 --> 00:31:00,030
because that's where the boat set out that night.

743
00:31:00,530 --> 00:31:01,510
Roeena didn't move.

744
00:31:01,850 --> 00:31:02,670
What night, Neve?

745
00:31:02,970 --> 00:31:03,490
The night.

746
00:31:04,070 --> 00:31:05,530
Neve wiped her hands on her apron.

747
00:31:05,890 --> 00:31:06,910
A mechanical gesture.

748
00:31:07,530 --> 00:31:08,370
The only night.

749
00:31:08,890 --> 00:31:11,010
The one this family could never bury properly.

750
00:31:11,470 --> 00:31:12,730
She turned her face aside.

751
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:14,670
Don't ask me for the rest dear.

752
00:31:15,090 --> 00:31:15,410
Please.

753
00:31:16,170 --> 00:31:17,310
Roeena swallowed hard.

754
00:31:17,670 --> 00:31:18,810
Mr. Kitt.

755
00:31:19,110 --> 00:31:19,870
Neve continued.

756
00:31:20,470 --> 00:31:22,990
And now she was speaking to the basil, not to her.

757
00:31:23,210 --> 00:31:24,370
At a way of laughing loud.

758
00:31:24,810 --> 00:31:27,210
Mrs. Udora used to say he'd wake the whole

759
00:31:27,210 --> 00:31:28,630
house when he was a child.

760
00:31:29,230 --> 00:31:31,250
A small smile crossed her face and vanished.

761
00:31:31,770 --> 00:31:32,910
It was a beautiful laugh.

762
00:31:33,270 --> 00:31:34,410
Too full for that mouth.

763
00:31:34,870 --> 00:31:35,710
You have his laugh.

764
00:31:36,270 --> 00:31:37,490
Roeena had to grip the counter.

765
00:31:38,090 --> 00:31:39,390
The air went out of her slowly.

766
00:31:39,890 --> 00:31:41,910
Her hand pressed on the cold marble.

767
00:31:42,410 --> 00:31:46,690
The certainty assembling inside her ribs like an old building rising from the dark.

768
00:31:47,090 --> 00:31:47,930
Whose laugh it was.

769
00:31:48,410 --> 00:31:49,810
Where the sentence came from.

770
00:31:50,010 --> 00:31:52,090
Why Udora had looked at her that way.

771
00:31:52,330 --> 00:31:54,150
As she left that night at the ball.

772
00:31:54,590 --> 00:31:55,330
Thank you, Neve.

773
00:31:55,870 --> 00:31:56,110
Dear.

774
00:31:56,110 --> 00:31:58,450
The housekeeper held her arm for a second.

775
00:31:58,830 --> 00:32:00,690
Her fingers were firm and dry.

776
00:32:01,210 --> 00:32:01,590
He suffered.

777
00:32:02,130 --> 00:32:03,890
Don't let anger make you forget that.

778
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:04,850
I won't forget.

779
00:32:05,410 --> 00:32:07,670
The weekend passed in a silence of war.

780
00:32:08,110 --> 00:32:09,910
Jego didn't try to enter the guest room.

781
00:32:10,350 --> 00:32:11,830
Roeena didn't come down from meals.

782
00:32:12,430 --> 00:32:14,210
Feeling carried trays in silence.

783
00:32:14,750 --> 00:32:15,970
Left them outside the door.

784
00:32:16,390 --> 00:32:17,530
Collected them untouched.

785
00:32:18,150 --> 00:32:20,970
On Saturday afternoon, Roeena wrote in her planner.

786
00:32:21,390 --> 00:32:23,310
The list of everything she needed to trace.

787
00:32:23,850 --> 00:32:24,270
Payments.

788
00:32:24,270 --> 00:32:25,330
Names.

789
00:32:25,750 --> 00:32:26,030
Cities.

790
00:32:26,790 --> 00:32:27,250
Dates.

791
00:32:27,850 --> 00:32:31,990
She started with the public library in downtown Savannah, where the old newspapers were

792
00:32:31,990 --> 00:32:33,170
kept on microfilm.

793
00:32:33,530 --> 00:32:36,630
She spent hours hunched over a reader that hummed softly.

794
00:32:37,090 --> 00:32:40,950
The smell of dry paper and old air conditioning filling the small room.

795
00:32:41,310 --> 00:32:43,210
She found the headline she knew existed.

796
00:32:43,730 --> 00:32:45,770
Quint Air Missing After Coastal Storm.

797
00:32:46,290 --> 00:32:48,130
The photo was small, grainy.

798
00:32:48,550 --> 00:32:50,690
A young man smiling with his mouth open.

799
00:32:50,970 --> 00:32:52,110
His teeth a little crooked.

800
00:32:52,110 --> 00:32:54,370
His hair touseled by the wind.

801
00:32:54,770 --> 00:32:56,630
She looked at the face for a long time.

802
00:32:57,030 --> 00:32:58,670
There was something of Jego in it.

803
00:32:58,850 --> 00:33:01,150
In the shape of the eyes in the line of the jaw.

804
00:33:01,610 --> 00:33:04,370
There was also that Frank Lough, Nieve, had described.

805
00:33:04,910 --> 00:33:08,130
Too wide for a newspaper portrait impossible to contain.

806
00:33:08,710 --> 00:33:11,390
On Sunday, she cross-referenced information.

807
00:33:11,870 --> 00:33:14,330
She asked feeling for old statements with some excuse.

808
00:33:14,910 --> 00:33:17,830
And the assistant, who already liked her more than he should,

809
00:33:18,310 --> 00:33:19,610
gave in without asking.

810
00:33:19,610 --> 00:33:23,670
She found regular payments going out of a parallel account of Jego's.

811
00:33:23,870 --> 00:33:24,310
Monthly.

812
00:33:24,790 --> 00:33:26,290
Always the same rounded amount.

813
00:33:26,770 --> 00:33:30,330
Always to the office of a lawyer with no recognizable family name.

814
00:33:30,670 --> 00:33:34,430
She found receipts from a pharmacy in a small town she'd never heard of.

815
00:33:34,530 --> 00:33:38,890
She found, among the clippings, Nieve kept in an old envelope in the kitchen cabinet.

816
00:33:39,470 --> 00:33:43,250
A photo, where a teenage kid appeared beside an older man.

817
00:33:43,690 --> 00:33:46,510
The same face she'd recognized in the more recent records.

818
00:33:46,510 --> 00:33:48,910
Marlo called it three in the morning on Monday.

819
00:33:49,450 --> 00:33:50,930
Roeena answered on the second ring.

820
00:33:51,470 --> 00:33:53,770
Roe, I had the strange feeling that you needed to laugh.

821
00:33:54,370 --> 00:33:54,630
Marlo.

822
00:33:55,270 --> 00:33:56,790
Seriously, I was asleep.

823
00:33:57,310 --> 00:33:58,230
Woke up out of nowhere.

824
00:33:58,550 --> 00:33:59,730
Looked at the ceiling and thought,

825
00:34:00,250 --> 00:34:02,450
this woman needs to laugh right now.

826
00:34:02,810 --> 00:34:03,570
Roeena laughed.

827
00:34:03,910 --> 00:34:07,470
She laughed for real mouth open in the middle of the silent guest room.

828
00:34:07,890 --> 00:34:09,970
Then she started to cry and kept laughing,

829
00:34:10,410 --> 00:34:12,370
and Marlo on the other end stayed quiet,

830
00:34:12,710 --> 00:34:14,270
waiting for the hurricane to pass.

831
00:34:14,270 --> 00:34:17,730
I found out the name Roeena said when she was able.

832
00:34:18,090 --> 00:34:19,930
The kid guy, he was his brother,

833
00:34:20,450 --> 00:34:22,610
was, that's what Silas said.

834
00:34:22,950 --> 00:34:25,430
Marlo breathed in deep and do you believe it?

835
00:34:25,630 --> 00:34:28,350
I believe nobody pays for a pharmacy for a dead man.

836
00:34:28,790 --> 00:34:29,910
Silas on the other end.

837
00:34:30,990 --> 00:34:33,910
Then, Roe, Marlo's voice was serious now.

838
00:34:34,170 --> 00:34:36,070
Are you sure you want to go down this hole?

839
00:34:36,510 --> 00:34:37,470
I already have.

840
00:34:37,730 --> 00:34:38,630
Then hold on tight.

841
00:34:39,110 --> 00:34:41,110
Roeena looked at the planner open on the mattress,

842
00:34:41,630 --> 00:34:43,850
and address had appeared twice in the receipts.

843
00:34:43,850 --> 00:34:46,470
A small town a few hours by train from Savannah,

844
00:34:47,070 --> 00:34:49,110
a name that matched the man from the old photo.

845
00:34:49,570 --> 00:34:51,290
She circled everything in red pen,

846
00:34:51,670 --> 00:34:53,490
and underlined the address three times,

847
00:34:53,910 --> 00:34:56,610
the pressure of the pen leaving a groove on the paper below.

848
00:34:57,110 --> 00:34:58,390
On the other side of the house,

849
00:34:58,810 --> 00:35:02,230
Jego was sitting in the study with a glass of whiskey he hadn't touched in hours.

850
00:35:02,670 --> 00:35:04,390
He'd heard the taxi arrive in the morning,

851
00:35:04,810 --> 00:35:06,030
he'd heard the taxi leave.

852
00:35:06,330 --> 00:35:08,510
He'd heard Roeena ask feeling for the statements,

853
00:35:09,110 --> 00:35:11,830
with an excuse he knew because he himself was the one,

854
00:35:11,830 --> 00:35:14,330
who'd used that excuse decades ago.

855
00:35:14,730 --> 00:35:16,170
He knew she was piecing it together.

856
00:35:16,550 --> 00:35:18,230
He knew she was going to find it,

857
00:35:18,470 --> 00:35:20,170
and for the first time in 10 years,

858
00:35:20,670 --> 00:35:23,030
he couldn't tell whether he was afraid of what she'd discover,

859
00:35:23,550 --> 00:35:25,650
or afraid of what he'd feel when she knew.

860
00:35:26,010 --> 00:35:27,570
He ran his hand over his forehead,

861
00:35:28,050 --> 00:35:28,970
his hand was trembling.

862
00:35:29,590 --> 00:35:31,910
In the guest room, Roeena closed the planner,

863
00:35:32,510 --> 00:35:35,430
a name, an address, a small town,

864
00:35:35,790 --> 00:35:37,150
everything that had come before.

865
00:35:37,590 --> 00:35:39,850
The old story, the charade at the ball, the coffee,

866
00:35:39,850 --> 00:35:42,770
without a recorder, had been training for this decision.

867
00:35:43,490 --> 00:35:45,610
She turned off the light, and in the dark,

868
00:35:45,830 --> 00:35:49,090
she heard clearly the sound the empty chair made inside her now.

869
00:35:49,430 --> 00:35:52,330
It was no longer a creek, it was a whole name.

870
00:35:54,090 --> 00:35:56,170
Chapter 4, The Town With No Name.

871
00:35:57,550 --> 00:35:59,110
In a scaven on Tuesday morning,

872
00:35:59,490 --> 00:36:01,610
and he gave in because Roeena stopped asking.

873
00:36:02,090 --> 00:36:03,910
She walked into his office without knocking.

874
00:36:04,370 --> 00:36:06,330
She placed the open planner on his desk,

875
00:36:06,770 --> 00:36:08,170
the address circled in red,

876
00:36:08,170 --> 00:36:11,850
the name of the man from the old photo written beside it.

877
00:36:12,150 --> 00:36:12,790
She said nothing.

878
00:36:13,410 --> 00:36:17,030
Silas read it, leaned back against the chair and closed his eyes for a moment,

879
00:36:17,430 --> 00:36:20,290
like someone who knew this moment would come sooner or later,

880
00:36:20,630 --> 00:36:21,890
and had chosen too late.

881
00:36:22,390 --> 00:36:23,670
You got to this on your own.

882
00:36:23,930 --> 00:36:26,110
I get to almost everything on my own, Silas.

883
00:36:26,650 --> 00:36:28,890
The open his eyes, there was guilt in them now.

884
00:36:29,190 --> 00:36:33,830
An old guilty no longer tried to disguise beneath the efficiency of the faithful assistant.

885
00:36:34,330 --> 00:36:35,890
If I complete the picture,

886
00:36:35,890 --> 00:36:37,590
Jago will kill me.

887
00:36:37,950 --> 00:36:40,570
Jago is already dying inside Silas.

888
00:36:41,070 --> 00:36:41,630
She said,

889
00:36:42,050 --> 00:36:42,710
what do you want?

890
00:36:43,090 --> 00:36:44,250
To bury both of them.

891
00:36:44,690 --> 00:36:46,730
Silas kept looking at her for a length of time

892
00:36:46,730 --> 00:36:50,290
that seemed to stretch beyond how long Silas usually lasts.

893
00:36:50,710 --> 00:36:52,190
Then he opened a desk drawer,

894
00:36:52,470 --> 00:36:54,490
and took out a small card no letterhead,

895
00:36:54,890 --> 00:36:57,030
with a name written by hand on one side,

896
00:36:57,410 --> 00:36:58,590
and an address on the other.

897
00:36:58,990 --> 00:37:01,050
He slid it across the desk with two fingers,

898
00:37:01,610 --> 00:37:03,270
like someone handing something over,

899
00:37:03,270 --> 00:37:06,650
and at the same time apologizing for having taken so long.

900
00:37:07,070 --> 00:37:09,070
The man who carries the money is this one.

901
00:37:09,310 --> 00:37:11,610
His voice came out low, almost horse.

902
00:37:12,070 --> 00:37:13,830
He lives between Savannah and the town.

903
00:37:14,190 --> 00:37:16,150
He makes the trip by train once a month,

904
00:37:16,570 --> 00:37:17,730
always on the first Saturday.

905
00:37:18,170 --> 00:37:19,410
He tapped the card lightly.

906
00:37:19,950 --> 00:37:21,910
Kid lives in that town under another name.

907
00:37:22,350 --> 00:37:23,630
I'm not going to tell you which.

908
00:37:23,990 --> 00:37:25,550
That he'll have to tell you himself,

909
00:37:26,150 --> 00:37:27,010
Ruinna took the card.

910
00:37:27,410 --> 00:37:29,250
She felt the paper way more than it should,

911
00:37:29,650 --> 00:37:31,750
more than any paper card should weigh.

912
00:37:32,170 --> 00:37:32,710
Thank you.

913
00:37:33,490 --> 00:37:36,510
Ruinna, Silas leaned forward his elbows on the desk.

914
00:37:36,930 --> 00:37:39,050
If he doesn't want to come back, don't force it.

915
00:37:39,190 --> 00:37:40,010
He has that right.

916
00:37:40,370 --> 00:37:41,570
I won't force it.

917
00:37:41,790 --> 00:37:45,610
And please, his voice nearly broke before reaching the end of the sentence.

918
00:37:46,130 --> 00:37:48,130
Take care of Jago when you come back.

919
00:37:48,490 --> 00:37:51,150
She tucked the card into the inside pocket of her bag.

920
00:37:51,490 --> 00:37:52,330
She stood up.

921
00:37:52,470 --> 00:37:54,590
She was almost at the door when he spoke again.

922
00:37:55,170 --> 00:37:56,330
Ruinna, yes.

923
00:37:56,890 --> 00:37:59,070
By now, why did you tell me now?

924
00:37:59,310 --> 00:38:00,510
He took a while to answer.

925
00:38:00,510 --> 00:38:03,050
When he answered, he looked at the window,

926
00:38:03,450 --> 00:38:04,310
not at her.

927
00:38:04,570 --> 00:38:06,650
At the street below where Savannah went on a head,

928
00:38:06,790 --> 00:38:07,410
knowing nothing.

929
00:38:07,830 --> 00:38:11,010
Because I watched Jago spend 10 years dying slowly,

930
00:38:11,450 --> 00:38:14,190
and I watched you arrive and him start to live again.

931
00:38:14,510 --> 00:38:17,330
And I can't watch him lose you thinking he's protecting you.

932
00:38:17,510 --> 00:38:19,030
He turned his gaze back to her.

933
00:38:19,310 --> 00:38:20,870
Someone needs to break this cycle.

934
00:38:21,290 --> 00:38:23,550
You're the only one with the courage to break it.

935
00:38:23,810 --> 00:38:24,970
Ruinna nodded once.

936
00:38:25,390 --> 00:38:25,870
She left.

937
00:38:26,570 --> 00:38:29,830
Outside Savannah's air had that humid mid-afternoon heat.

938
00:38:29,830 --> 00:38:34,970
Dense and green, with the smell of wet earth mixed with the distant salt of the

939
00:38:34,970 --> 00:38:35,370
estuary.

940
00:38:35,830 --> 00:38:37,630
She walked to the station without hurry,

941
00:38:38,150 --> 00:38:40,130
feeling the uneven paving under her shoes.

942
00:38:40,750 --> 00:38:42,370
The sounds of the city around her.

943
00:38:42,550 --> 00:38:46,070
The street car passing by, a child shouting in some backyard.

944
00:38:46,590 --> 00:38:48,590
The clinking of glasses in a corner cafe.

945
00:38:49,150 --> 00:38:51,310
She bought a one-way ticket for the four-ocluck train,

946
00:38:51,810 --> 00:38:53,350
and called Marlo from the payphone.

947
00:38:53,810 --> 00:38:54,270
I'm going.

948
00:38:54,870 --> 00:38:55,110
Alone?

949
00:38:55,730 --> 00:38:56,070
Alone.

950
00:38:56,710 --> 00:38:58,470
Marlo paused for a long time.

951
00:38:58,470 --> 00:39:01,790
The kind that contains questions one decides not to ask.

952
00:39:02,190 --> 00:39:05,770
Do you want me to call someone if you don't come back in 24 hours?

953
00:39:06,150 --> 00:39:07,050
Call Silas.

954
00:39:07,370 --> 00:39:07,570
Done.

955
00:39:08,150 --> 00:39:08,750
Before boarding.

956
00:39:09,410 --> 00:39:11,110
Ruinna stopped at the house near the river.

957
00:39:11,550 --> 00:39:12,950
She came in through the side door.

958
00:39:13,330 --> 00:39:16,150
Went up to the guest room through some clothes into a small suitcase,

959
00:39:16,870 --> 00:39:20,190
with the objectivity of someone who knows that thinking too much

960
00:39:20,190 --> 00:39:22,550
is a luxury that doesn't fit in the luggage.

961
00:39:23,070 --> 00:39:27,370
She went down to the kitchen, where the afternoon light came in slanted through the shutters,

962
00:39:27,370 --> 00:39:30,170
and drew thin stripes across the stone floor,

963
00:39:30,570 --> 00:39:32,970
and wrote a short letter on a piece of writing paper.

964
00:39:33,430 --> 00:39:34,750
The letter had a single line.

965
00:39:35,170 --> 00:39:37,710
I'll come back when I bring what he couldn't bring on his own.

966
00:39:38,030 --> 00:39:40,070
She left the letter on top of the day's newspaper.

967
00:39:40,550 --> 00:39:41,050
She left.

968
00:39:41,610 --> 00:39:43,970
Feline saw her come down the stairs with the suitcase,

969
00:39:44,510 --> 00:39:45,330
and asked nothing.

970
00:39:45,790 --> 00:39:47,170
She asked him to call a taxi.

971
00:39:47,730 --> 00:39:48,530
He called one.

972
00:39:48,890 --> 00:39:50,230
Before the taxi door closed,

973
00:39:50,630 --> 00:39:52,870
the assistant said quietly almost to himself,

974
00:39:53,290 --> 00:39:54,370
have a good trip miss.

975
00:39:54,710 --> 00:39:55,810
She didn't correct him.

976
00:39:55,810 --> 00:39:58,630
The train left Savannah at four o'clock sharp.

977
00:39:59,210 --> 00:40:00,710
Roenachosa seat by the window,

978
00:40:01,230 --> 00:40:03,470
and rested her forehead against the cold glass,

979
00:40:03,930 --> 00:40:05,710
and for a long time thought about nothing.

980
00:40:06,150 --> 00:40:08,610
She passed low houses, flooded fields,

981
00:40:09,210 --> 00:40:11,750
a small town with a rusty water tower in the center,

982
00:40:12,350 --> 00:40:13,590
a river that wasn't the Savannah,

983
00:40:14,190 --> 00:40:18,070
a line of Cyprus's cutting into the copper-coloured sky of the late afternoon.

984
00:40:18,710 --> 00:40:20,370
The sun began to set slowly,

985
00:40:20,930 --> 00:40:23,590
tinting the landscape and orange that looked like a painting.

986
00:40:23,590 --> 00:40:26,750
She opened the planner and re-read the address three times

987
00:40:26,750 --> 00:40:28,530
as if she could forget it,

988
00:40:28,630 --> 00:40:29,990
and she knew she couldn't.

989
00:40:30,350 --> 00:40:32,230
On the other side at the house near the river,

990
00:40:32,810 --> 00:40:34,490
Jager arrived at seven at night

991
00:40:34,490 --> 00:40:37,650
and felt that something was missing before he looked in any direction.

992
00:40:38,150 --> 00:40:40,070
It was as if the house had changed weight,

993
00:40:40,450 --> 00:40:43,270
not temperature, not sound, weight.

994
00:40:43,790 --> 00:40:45,630
He passed through the living room the kitchen,

995
00:40:46,110 --> 00:40:47,690
saw the letter on top of the newspaper.

996
00:40:48,270 --> 00:40:49,150
He read it.

997
00:40:49,270 --> 00:40:50,250
He read it again,

998
00:40:50,250 --> 00:40:54,650
and something in him collapsed with the same silent precision of a structure

999
00:40:54,650 --> 00:40:56,510
that gives way from within,

1000
00:40:56,950 --> 00:40:58,270
with no visible warning.

1001
00:40:58,790 --> 00:41:01,390
It was the same old night returning to his nostrils,

1002
00:41:01,950 --> 00:41:03,590
the smell of the sea after the storm,

1003
00:41:04,110 --> 00:41:05,570
the taste of metal in his mouth,

1004
00:41:06,050 --> 00:41:08,710
the physical animal certainty that he had lost again,

1005
00:41:09,070 --> 00:41:12,610
and that this time the punishment was proportional to the size of the mistake.

1006
00:41:13,090 --> 00:41:14,210
He let the letter drop.

1007
00:41:14,530 --> 00:41:15,850
He sat on the kitchen floor.

1008
00:41:16,330 --> 00:41:17,070
He truly sat.

1009
00:41:17,410 --> 00:41:19,390
His back against the door of the low cabinet

1010
00:41:19,390 --> 00:41:21,430
and his hands open on his knees

1011
00:41:21,430 --> 00:41:23,590
as if he didn't know what to do with them.

1012
00:41:23,890 --> 00:41:25,810
He stayed there too long for it to be dignity.

1013
00:41:26,250 --> 00:41:27,890
Scyl is showed up half an hour later.

1014
00:41:28,310 --> 00:41:30,290
He hadn't been called, he simply knew.

1015
00:41:30,630 --> 00:41:32,110
He came in through the side door,

1016
00:41:32,490 --> 00:41:33,630
found Jager on the floor,

1017
00:41:33,790 --> 00:41:35,350
knelt beside him without hesitation.

1018
00:41:35,990 --> 00:41:36,850
I told her,

1019
00:41:37,190 --> 00:41:38,850
Jager raised his face slowly.

1020
00:41:39,370 --> 00:41:41,670
There was something in his eyes that wasn't anger.

1021
00:41:42,130 --> 00:41:43,810
It was an exhaustion so deep,

1022
00:41:44,010 --> 00:41:45,570
it passed beneath the anger,

1023
00:41:45,850 --> 00:41:48,130
and reached a place the anger no longer reached.

1024
00:41:48,130 --> 00:41:49,630
You told her what,

1025
00:41:49,890 --> 00:41:50,430
the name,

1026
00:41:50,910 --> 00:41:51,470
the address,

1027
00:41:52,050 --> 00:41:53,870
the man who carries the money.

1028
00:41:54,250 --> 00:41:55,370
Jager closed his eyes.

1029
00:41:55,790 --> 00:41:57,730
It took him a full second to breathe again.

1030
00:41:58,150 --> 00:41:59,390
I'm going to hit you siless.

1031
00:41:59,930 --> 00:42:00,410
Hit me.

1032
00:42:00,830 --> 00:42:01,950
Jager didn't hit him.

1033
00:42:02,250 --> 00:42:03,770
He clenched his fist, raised it,

1034
00:42:03,770 --> 00:42:06,230
and the fist stopped in the air before touching anything.

1035
00:42:06,670 --> 00:42:07,950
He lowered his hands slowly,

1036
00:42:08,510 --> 00:42:09,530
rested it on his knee,

1037
00:42:09,890 --> 00:42:11,350
and stared at his own fingers,

1038
00:42:11,710 --> 00:42:13,330
as if he didn't recognize them.

1039
00:42:13,550 --> 00:42:15,830
As if that man sitting on the floor of his kitchen

1040
00:42:15,830 --> 00:42:17,130
belonged to someone else.

1041
00:42:17,130 --> 00:42:18,370
She went alone.

1042
00:42:18,830 --> 00:42:19,470
She did,

1043
00:42:19,790 --> 00:42:21,210
and if he doesn't take her in.

1044
00:42:21,530 --> 00:42:22,430
He'll take her in.

1045
00:42:22,770 --> 00:42:24,410
He can't say no to anyone, Jager.

1046
00:42:24,910 --> 00:42:25,830
He never could.

1047
00:42:26,130 --> 00:42:27,350
Jager swallowed twice.

1048
00:42:27,750 --> 00:42:29,990
And if he takes her in and doesn't want to come?

1049
00:42:30,390 --> 00:42:31,370
Silas didn't answer.

1050
00:42:31,810 --> 00:42:32,970
There was no answer to that.

1051
00:42:33,370 --> 00:42:34,950
Jager squeezed his eyes shut.

1052
00:42:35,570 --> 00:42:38,210
Inside something in him was reconstructing the timeline

1053
00:42:38,210 --> 00:42:40,010
with a precision that hurt.

1054
00:42:40,450 --> 00:42:41,330
The train's schedule,

1055
00:42:41,750 --> 00:42:42,250
the distance,

1056
00:42:42,750 --> 00:42:44,090
the time she'd need to arrive.

1057
00:42:44,650 --> 00:42:46,650
The night she'd spend alone in a town he knew

1058
00:42:46,650 --> 00:42:48,330
from a map and from receipts,

1059
00:42:48,570 --> 00:42:49,910
but never with his own eyes.

1060
00:42:50,470 --> 00:42:51,130
He'd never gone.

1061
00:42:51,570 --> 00:42:53,170
He'd never allowed himself to go,

1062
00:42:53,390 --> 00:42:54,890
and now she was going for him.

1063
00:42:55,110 --> 00:42:57,050
With the courage he'd traded for control,

1064
00:42:57,530 --> 00:42:59,010
and he was sitting on the kitchen floor

1065
00:42:59,010 --> 00:43:01,750
because he no longer knew what to do with his own body.

1066
00:43:02,250 --> 00:43:02,610
Silas.

1067
00:43:03,190 --> 00:43:03,490
Yes.

1068
00:43:03,970 --> 00:43:05,030
If she comes back,

1069
00:43:05,310 --> 00:43:06,130
I'll fix it.

1070
00:43:06,430 --> 00:43:07,310
She'll come back.

1071
00:43:07,610 --> 00:43:08,670
If she comes back.

1072
00:43:09,150 --> 00:43:11,650
Silas rested his hand on his shoulder and left it there.

1073
00:43:11,850 --> 00:43:12,750
She'll come back, Jager.

1074
00:43:13,210 --> 00:43:16,230
In the small town, the train arrived at 9.20 at night.

1075
00:43:16,230 --> 00:43:18,410
Roina got off with the small suitcase,

1076
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:20,790
felt the asphalt different under her feet,

1077
00:43:21,470 --> 00:43:23,330
quieter without savanna's constant noise,

1078
00:43:23,810 --> 00:43:26,230
and looked for a small hotel a block from the station,

1079
00:43:26,710 --> 00:43:30,730
with painted wooden windows and a ceiling fan that turned slowly.

1080
00:43:31,190 --> 00:43:32,410
She paid for one night,

1081
00:43:32,790 --> 00:43:34,370
went up, didn't have dinner.

1082
00:43:34,830 --> 00:43:36,730
She sat on the edge of the bed until dawn,

1083
00:43:37,110 --> 00:43:39,950
with Silas's card in her hand and the address memorized.

1084
00:43:40,510 --> 00:43:42,930
In the morning, she followed the map on foot.

1085
00:43:43,390 --> 00:43:45,010
The town was smaller than she'd expected,

1086
00:43:45,010 --> 00:43:47,130
a main street with five shops,

1087
00:43:47,590 --> 00:43:51,250
a central square with a bandstand painted white and peeling at the edges,

1088
00:43:51,690 --> 00:43:55,190
low houses scattered along dirt roads where grass grew down the middle.

1089
00:43:55,570 --> 00:43:58,190
The address led her to a modest light blue house,

1090
00:43:58,530 --> 00:43:59,910
with an neglected front garden,

1091
00:44:00,430 --> 00:44:02,870
and a rocking chair sitting motionless on the porch.

1092
00:44:03,350 --> 00:44:04,390
She knocked on the door,

1093
00:44:04,890 --> 00:44:06,410
once with her knuckle, firm.

1094
00:44:06,990 --> 00:44:08,130
A man opened it.

1095
00:44:08,390 --> 00:44:10,450
She recognized him before she looked properly.

1096
00:44:10,910 --> 00:44:12,990
She recognized him by the shape of the eyes,

1097
00:44:12,990 --> 00:44:14,690
by the line of the jaw,

1098
00:44:15,030 --> 00:44:16,570
by the way he stood in the doorway.

1099
00:44:17,190 --> 00:44:19,350
The same way Jago had a filling a threshold

1100
00:44:19,350 --> 00:44:22,490
that presence that filled the space even in silence.

1101
00:44:23,150 --> 00:44:25,870
Except, this man was thinner, harder,

1102
00:44:26,370 --> 00:44:29,750
with a small scar crossing his left eyebrow and lighter hair.

1103
00:44:30,010 --> 00:44:30,650
Sun bleached.

1104
00:44:31,190 --> 00:44:34,450
He had the slightly crooked teeth she remembered from the newspaper photo.

1105
00:44:35,030 --> 00:44:37,730
Kit, he was paralyzed for a full second,

1106
00:44:38,150 --> 00:44:39,670
then he stepped back half a step,

1107
00:44:39,670 --> 00:44:40,930
who are you?

1108
00:44:41,410 --> 00:44:43,390
Rowena Pike, she didn't move forward.

1109
00:44:43,830 --> 00:44:45,430
I've been with your brother for a while.

1110
00:44:45,910 --> 00:44:48,070
The silence that came after was dense and loaded.

1111
00:44:48,690 --> 00:44:50,410
Kit rested one hand on the door frame,

1112
00:44:50,750 --> 00:44:52,030
as if he needed the support,

1113
00:44:52,550 --> 00:44:54,410
his fingers gripping the painted wood.

1114
00:44:54,810 --> 00:44:55,850
You shouldn't be here.

1115
00:44:56,110 --> 00:44:56,570
I know.

1116
00:44:57,030 --> 00:44:57,670
He sent you.

1117
00:44:58,030 --> 00:44:59,710
He doesn't even know I came.

1118
00:45:00,070 --> 00:45:01,450
Kit looked at her for a long time.

1119
00:45:01,790 --> 00:45:03,610
The physical shock was still in him,

1120
00:45:03,830 --> 00:45:05,390
and the old anger rose automatically,

1121
00:45:06,030 --> 00:45:08,250
and the fear hidden beneath the anger too,

1122
00:45:08,250 --> 00:45:09,750
and there was something else,

1123
00:45:10,370 --> 00:45:12,550
deeper, that he could no longer name well.

1124
00:45:12,870 --> 00:45:13,870
Then he stepped aside.

1125
00:45:14,430 --> 00:45:15,070
Come in.

1126
00:45:15,370 --> 00:45:17,190
The living room was small and clean,

1127
00:45:17,710 --> 00:45:20,910
with that silence of a place where a person has lived alone for too long.

1128
00:45:21,330 --> 00:45:22,630
There was a dark wooden table,

1129
00:45:23,050 --> 00:45:26,450
two chairs, a sofa with warm fabric on the backrest,

1130
00:45:26,890 --> 00:45:29,210
a shelf with few books and no ornaments.

1131
00:45:29,870 --> 00:45:31,430
Kit pointed to one of the chairs.

1132
00:45:31,950 --> 00:45:36,010
Rowena sat, he stayed standing leaning against the wall arms crossed.

1133
00:45:36,010 --> 00:45:36,650
Talk.

1134
00:45:37,170 --> 00:45:37,670
She talked.

1135
00:45:38,190 --> 00:45:39,570
She talked for a long time,

1136
00:45:39,950 --> 00:45:41,550
without embellishing, without crying.

1137
00:45:41,990 --> 00:45:45,290
She talked about the investigators Jago had hired over the years.

1138
00:45:45,710 --> 00:45:48,490
About the money he left with lawyers who had no names,

1139
00:45:49,030 --> 00:45:51,530
about the medications paid for by third parties.

1140
00:45:51,890 --> 00:45:54,190
The debts settled before they became dangerous.

1141
00:45:54,770 --> 00:45:58,410
About the empty chair no one explained and no one removed from the living room.

1142
00:45:58,630 --> 00:45:59,750
She talked about Yudora,

1143
00:46:00,270 --> 00:46:02,010
about the way she never said his name.

1144
00:46:02,470 --> 00:46:05,810
About the way once on the porch she had murmured about a lost laugh.

1145
00:46:05,810 --> 00:46:08,210
She talked about the terrace Jago avoided.

1146
00:46:08,710 --> 00:46:10,590
She talked about the envelope he'd hidden.

1147
00:46:11,070 --> 00:46:13,290
About the control he confused with love.

1148
00:46:13,710 --> 00:46:16,850
About the old fear he carried because he thought that if he let go,

1149
00:46:17,150 --> 00:46:18,450
he'd lose everything again.

1150
00:46:18,910 --> 00:46:20,350
Kit listened without interrupting.

1151
00:46:20,990 --> 00:46:23,490
When she finished, he stayed silent for a while.

1152
00:46:23,810 --> 00:46:24,530
Then he laughed.

1153
00:46:25,050 --> 00:46:26,650
A short, dry laugh.

1154
00:46:27,050 --> 00:46:27,890
Almost a grunt.

1155
00:46:28,250 --> 00:46:29,990
He spent 10 years looking for me.

1156
00:46:30,210 --> 00:46:30,750
He did.

1157
00:46:31,150 --> 00:46:31,850
Without stopping.

1158
00:46:32,350 --> 00:46:33,030
Without stopping.

1159
00:46:33,570 --> 00:46:34,830
And he never came himself.

1160
00:46:34,830 --> 00:46:36,130
Roena hesitated.

1161
00:46:36,650 --> 00:46:38,570
He thought you didn't want to be found by him.

1162
00:46:38,830 --> 00:46:39,830
Kit closed his eyes.

1163
00:46:40,330 --> 00:46:43,730
Inside something that had been hard for 10 years began to crack.

1164
00:46:44,230 --> 00:46:46,310
Slow and inevitable as a crack in stone.

1165
00:46:46,910 --> 00:46:47,650
He swallowed once.

1166
00:46:48,090 --> 00:46:48,690
swallowed again.

1167
00:46:49,230 --> 00:46:49,910
He wasn't wrong.

1168
00:46:50,350 --> 00:46:50,970
He was.

1169
00:46:51,510 --> 00:46:52,710
Roena's voice came out lower.

1170
00:46:53,230 --> 00:46:54,650
He just didn't know he was.

1171
00:46:54,970 --> 00:46:56,610
Kit peeled himself off the wall.

1172
00:46:57,010 --> 00:46:57,910
He went to the window.

1173
00:46:58,450 --> 00:47:04,810
Looked at the neglected garden for a long time at the grass growing between the

1174
00:47:04,810 --> 00:47:05,650
cowl-mate coffee.

1175
00:47:05,970 --> 00:47:07,910
They spent the afternoon and the night talking.

1176
00:47:08,390 --> 00:47:12,390
On the porch with cups that went cold twice in the sound of crickets filling the dark around

1177
00:47:12,390 --> 00:47:15,590
them, Kit spoke aloud for the first time about what he felt.

1178
00:47:16,030 --> 00:47:18,870
He said he'd fled because he thought he wasn't important to anyone.

1179
00:47:19,350 --> 00:47:22,990
But on that night, he'd asked his brother for help and his brother hadn't come.

1180
00:47:23,510 --> 00:47:27,470
And he understood, in that instant, that his world was worth less than a meeting.

1181
00:47:27,870 --> 00:47:32,470
That when the boat began to crack in the storm, he had two seconds to choose between swimming

1182
00:47:32,470 --> 00:47:33,110
or sinking.

1183
00:47:33,630 --> 00:47:36,550
And he chose to swim because the anger was greater than the exhaustion.

1184
00:47:37,190 --> 00:47:41,610
That when he came out the other side, on a stretch of beach he didn't even know where it was.

1185
00:47:42,030 --> 00:47:45,830
He made the decision to disappear because he thought no one would miss him enough to really

1186
00:47:45,830 --> 00:47:46,190
look.

1187
00:47:46,610 --> 00:47:51,010
And he looked, Kit said, looking at the bandstand in the square in the distance.

1188
00:47:51,610 --> 00:47:52,710
All these years.

1189
00:47:53,210 --> 00:47:54,450
All these years.

1190
00:47:54,890 --> 00:47:56,870
Kit ran his hand over his eyes slowly.

1191
00:47:57,390 --> 00:47:59,270
He made a mistake out of fear, Kit.

1192
00:47:59,270 --> 00:48:00,550
Not out of choice.

1193
00:48:00,930 --> 00:48:03,850
Browiness spoke low, looking at the same point he was.

1194
00:48:04,190 --> 00:48:05,690
He's afraid of you all the time.

1195
00:48:06,070 --> 00:48:08,410
Of what happened, and of what he didn't do.

1196
00:48:08,810 --> 00:48:09,790
Kit laughed again.

1197
00:48:10,130 --> 00:48:13,470
This time without the dryness of before, almost with affection.

1198
00:48:14,070 --> 00:48:16,510
And affection he clearly hadn't expected to feel.

1199
00:48:16,930 --> 00:48:19,470
You talk about him as if you knew him.

1200
00:48:19,750 --> 00:48:20,630
I know him.

1201
00:48:20,850 --> 00:48:21,610
You love him.

1202
00:48:21,850 --> 00:48:22,610
She didn't answer.

1203
00:48:23,110 --> 00:48:24,150
She didn't need to.

1204
00:48:24,450 --> 00:48:25,810
They stayed silent for a while.

1205
00:48:25,810 --> 00:48:29,390
With the warm wind passing through the branches of the old Magnolia,

1206
00:48:29,930 --> 00:48:31,430
growing in the corner of the garden,

1207
00:48:32,030 --> 00:48:34,550
then Kit spoke, looking at his own hands.

1208
00:48:35,050 --> 00:48:37,030
If I come back, I come back once.

1209
00:48:37,530 --> 00:48:38,110
No promises.

1210
00:48:38,730 --> 00:48:40,710
If it doesn't work, I leave again.

1211
00:48:41,170 --> 00:48:43,150
And this time no one finds me.

1212
00:48:43,390 --> 00:48:43,850
Agreed.

1213
00:48:44,250 --> 00:48:46,390
And I don't know if I'll be able to look at him.

1214
00:48:46,650 --> 00:48:48,090
You don't need to know that now.

1215
00:48:48,550 --> 00:48:51,790
Kit nodded slowly, like someone making a deal with himself,

1216
00:48:52,130 --> 00:48:53,110
as much as with her.

1217
00:48:53,110 --> 00:48:54,990
In the morning he took a small suitcase.

1218
00:48:55,750 --> 00:48:56,550
Very small.

1219
00:48:56,930 --> 00:49:00,190
Rowina looked at that suitcase and understood the size of what he carried.

1220
00:49:00,730 --> 00:49:03,770
Not in what was inside, but in how little there was.

1221
00:49:04,250 --> 00:49:07,710
Before they left for the station, she sent a single message to Silas,

1222
00:49:08,110 --> 00:49:09,570
from the telegraph on the corner.

1223
00:49:10,010 --> 00:49:12,070
We arrived tomorrow, prepare you Dora.

1224
00:49:12,550 --> 00:49:16,150
While they waited for the train on the wooden bench of the town's only platform,

1225
00:49:16,790 --> 00:49:18,830
Kit looked at the horizon and said,

1226
00:49:18,830 --> 00:49:22,630
without turning his face, Rowina, yes,

1227
00:49:23,150 --> 00:49:25,590
if you brought me here for him, he swallowed.

1228
00:49:26,170 --> 00:49:27,810
Thank you, she didn't answer.

1229
00:49:28,250 --> 00:49:32,130
She simply rested her hand over his hand, and his hand was cold,

1230
00:49:32,650 --> 00:49:33,890
and hers was too.

1231
00:49:34,310 --> 00:49:36,590
The train whistled in the...

1232
00:49:36,590 --> 00:49:39,170
Chapter 5, 10 years in a single room.

1233
00:49:40,450 --> 00:49:40,810
Distance.

1234
00:49:41,370 --> 00:49:42,370
Jego didn't sleep.

1235
00:49:42,910 --> 00:49:45,230
The house near the Savannah River was so silent

1236
00:49:45,230 --> 00:49:47,670
that he could hear his own pulse in his throat,

1237
00:49:47,670 --> 00:49:50,190
sitting on the study floor leaning against the shelf,

1238
00:49:50,590 --> 00:49:53,650
his suit rumpled and his tie loose since the small hours.

1239
00:49:53,950 --> 00:49:56,470
He counted time by the way the light came through the window.

1240
00:49:56,990 --> 00:50:02,570
First blue, then gray, then a timid goal that arrived to insulting for the weight of the day.

1241
00:50:02,990 --> 00:50:05,090
Rowina's letter was still folded in his lap.

1242
00:50:05,450 --> 00:50:07,990
He no longer needed to reread it to know what was written.

1243
00:50:08,470 --> 00:50:11,250
I'll come back when I bring what he couldn't bring on his own.

1244
00:50:11,510 --> 00:50:13,410
Each word weighed more than the last.

1245
00:50:13,830 --> 00:50:16,530
Each word opened a door he'd kept closed for 10 years,

1246
00:50:16,530 --> 00:50:19,210
and pushed him inside it with no choice, no warning,

1247
00:50:19,790 --> 00:50:21,490
without even letting him breathe first.

1248
00:50:21,950 --> 00:50:26,430
Inside, Jego had the cold certainty that the punishment had finally arrived,

1249
00:50:26,930 --> 00:50:29,810
not in the form of scandal, not in the form of death,

1250
00:50:30,230 --> 00:50:34,970
not in the form of a headline, in the form of a woman with an ink scar in the Sunday paper,

1251
00:50:35,310 --> 00:50:37,530
going after what he hadn't had the courage to bring.

1252
00:50:37,910 --> 00:50:39,970
And in the most cowardly part of him,

1253
00:50:40,150 --> 00:50:42,430
a low voice said that this scar could open again,

1254
00:50:42,850 --> 00:50:45,130
that this time the woman too might not come back.

1255
00:50:45,130 --> 00:50:47,390
Silas came in at seven without knocking.

1256
00:50:47,850 --> 00:50:49,790
He brought coffee Jego hadn't asked for,

1257
00:50:49,990 --> 00:50:51,710
and a silenced Jego didn't want.

1258
00:50:52,130 --> 00:50:56,490
He stood in the door frame waiting with that lawyer's patience of someone who'd already seen too many

1259
00:50:56,490 --> 00:50:58,150
clients on the floor of his own office.

1260
00:50:58,710 --> 00:51:00,850
Talk, Jego said without looking up.

1261
00:51:01,010 --> 00:51:02,630
She arrived, she's with him.

1262
00:51:02,930 --> 00:51:03,630
How do you know?

1263
00:51:03,990 --> 00:51:04,950
She sent me a message.

1264
00:51:05,530 --> 00:51:11,010
Short, Silas hesitated, and at the bottom of that hesitation there was an old guilt the lawyer had

1265
00:51:11,010 --> 00:51:13,250
decided to carry in silence until now.

1266
00:51:13,530 --> 00:51:14,550
He held out the phone.

1267
00:51:14,550 --> 00:51:18,990
Jego read the line on the screen and took a full second to breathe again.

1268
00:51:19,610 --> 00:51:20,550
We arrived tomorrow.

1269
00:51:21,250 --> 00:51:22,170
Prepare you dora.

1270
00:51:22,630 --> 00:51:23,590
He closed his eyes.

1271
00:51:24,130 --> 00:51:26,870
He felt the room spin as if someone had flipped the floor.

1272
00:51:27,290 --> 00:51:30,930
There was a man inside him who wanted to yell at Silas for giving up the thread.

1273
00:51:31,430 --> 00:51:34,690
There was another deeper who wanted to kneel and give thanks.

1274
00:51:35,170 --> 00:51:36,930
The first one for half a second.

1275
00:51:37,470 --> 00:51:42,710
Jego stood up, grabbed Silas by the lapel, and stopped his fist in the air before it closed.

1276
00:51:42,710 --> 00:51:45,030
His hand trembled, it never trembled.

1277
00:51:45,570 --> 00:51:47,610
Don't hit, Silas said very low.

1278
00:51:47,970 --> 00:51:49,310
You're not a man who hits.

1279
00:51:49,690 --> 00:51:52,150
I'm not a man of anything right now, Jego answered.

1280
00:51:52,670 --> 00:51:56,090
And let go of the lapel like someone releasing a rope too hot to hold.

1281
00:51:56,550 --> 00:51:57,330
They stood still.

1282
00:51:57,830 --> 00:52:03,050
Outside a bird insisted on a whistle of three repeated notes without tiring, without mercy.

1283
00:52:03,650 --> 00:52:06,610
Jego looked at his own reflection in the glass of the picture frame,

1284
00:52:07,070 --> 00:52:12,250
and recognized neither the disheveled hair, nor the civilised despair his eyes held.

1285
00:52:12,250 --> 00:52:16,210
Prepare her, he asked, and his voice didn't quite obey.

1286
00:52:16,710 --> 00:52:17,470
Prepare my mother.

1287
00:52:17,870 --> 00:52:18,310
I will.

1288
00:52:18,890 --> 00:52:19,290
Silas.

1289
00:52:19,790 --> 00:52:20,430
Jego swallowed.

1290
00:52:21,050 --> 00:52:21,710
Thank you.

1291
00:52:22,030 --> 00:52:23,190
Silas looked at him long.

1292
00:52:23,650 --> 00:52:24,390
He said nothing.

1293
00:52:24,930 --> 00:52:25,230
He left.

1294
00:52:25,770 --> 00:52:28,210
It was feeling who arrived first at the quint mentioned.

1295
00:52:28,810 --> 00:52:30,810
Udora was having tea in the small parlor.

1296
00:52:31,090 --> 00:52:33,830
The newspaper still untouched on the white linen napkin.

1297
00:52:34,310 --> 00:52:35,830
The matriarch looked up and read.

1298
00:52:36,170 --> 00:52:40,010
In the younger systems posture, that something was coming before the words.

1299
00:52:40,010 --> 00:52:41,310
She didn't ask.

1300
00:52:41,730 --> 00:52:45,410
She waited, with that old skill of letting Silas do the work.

1301
00:52:45,830 --> 00:52:49,530
Mrs Rowena asked that you come to the main hall at five.

1302
00:52:49,790 --> 00:52:53,950
Feline said, with the trained delicacy of someone delivering news he didn't understand.

1303
00:52:54,550 --> 00:52:56,190
And Mr. Jego as well.

1304
00:52:56,470 --> 00:52:59,650
Udora folded the newspaper carefully as if it might break.

1305
00:52:59,990 --> 00:53:04,310
Her hand, when it rested on the table, had a strange lightness for the weight of the day.

1306
00:53:04,690 --> 00:53:05,230
That's all?

1307
00:53:05,590 --> 00:53:06,490
She wanted to know.

1308
00:53:06,870 --> 00:53:07,470
That's all.

1309
00:53:07,830 --> 00:53:09,310
The matriarch didn't smile.

1310
00:53:09,310 --> 00:53:10,630
She didn't protest.

1311
00:53:11,170 --> 00:53:13,830
She nodded once and turned her gaze to the window.

1312
00:53:14,330 --> 00:53:17,390
Where the garden trees swayed in a breeze no one inside could feel.

1313
00:53:17,830 --> 00:53:19,190
The trainer arrived at four.

1314
00:53:19,670 --> 00:53:23,490
Rowena got off on the savanna platform with the same small bag she'd left with.

1315
00:53:23,790 --> 00:53:27,810
And a thin man beside her who insisted on keeping three steps of distance.

1316
00:53:28,330 --> 00:53:32,650
Like someone still deciding whether to stay, or turn around and disappear again.

1317
00:53:33,110 --> 00:53:34,270
Kitt had his head down.

1318
00:53:34,590 --> 00:53:35,810
His cap pulled low.

1319
00:53:36,130 --> 00:53:38,790
His backpack held tight against his chest like a shield.

1320
00:53:38,790 --> 00:53:41,930
Every sudden noise in the station made his jaw clench.

1321
00:53:42,270 --> 00:53:44,090
He stopped twice on the way to the taxi.

1322
00:53:44,570 --> 00:53:47,170
And both times Rowena pretended not to see,

1323
00:53:47,850 --> 00:53:49,950
continuing to walk at a pace that demanded nothing.

1324
00:53:50,490 --> 00:53:51,330
We can go back.

1325
00:53:51,530 --> 00:53:54,090
She said, at the third stop, without pressure.

1326
00:53:54,610 --> 00:53:56,730
If you want to go back now, we go back.

1327
00:53:56,990 --> 00:53:59,690
I'll take you back and won't tell anyone you set foot in savanna.

1328
00:54:00,210 --> 00:54:00,810
Kitt swallowed.

1329
00:54:01,290 --> 00:54:02,130
It's not that.

1330
00:54:02,430 --> 00:54:03,250
It's what then.

1331
00:54:03,570 --> 00:54:05,550
It's that I forgot what the smell is like.

1332
00:54:06,050 --> 00:54:07,010
Rowena looked at him.

1333
00:54:07,010 --> 00:54:10,050
There was an 18-year-old boy inside that thin man,

1334
00:54:10,390 --> 00:54:14,930
and the boy was blinking hard not to cry on the sidewalk of a station full of strangers.

1335
00:54:15,470 --> 00:54:16,650
She didn't touch his arm.

1336
00:54:16,910 --> 00:54:18,830
She just stood there at the same height waiting.

1337
00:54:19,330 --> 00:54:21,030
The smell is the same, she answered.

1338
00:54:21,690 --> 00:54:23,170
Magnolia and old money.

1339
00:54:23,650 --> 00:54:24,210
Kitt laughed.

1340
00:54:24,730 --> 00:54:26,530
A quick laugh, almost a sob.

1341
00:54:27,030 --> 00:54:27,330
Ah!

1342
00:54:27,810 --> 00:54:28,710
So it's the same.

1343
00:54:29,110 --> 00:54:30,170
They got into the taxi.

1344
00:54:30,750 --> 00:54:33,110
Rowena told the driver to stop at the door.

1345
00:54:33,430 --> 00:54:35,150
Chapter 6 The Chair with Anona.

1346
00:54:36,430 --> 00:54:37,230
The mansion.

1347
00:54:37,750 --> 00:54:39,090
Not at the house near the river.

1348
00:54:39,550 --> 00:54:41,510
Kitt raised his face when the facade appeared.

1349
00:54:42,030 --> 00:54:45,410
That heavy iron gate he knew better than any other place in the world.

1350
00:54:45,790 --> 00:54:47,570
He stared at it for a long time.

1351
00:54:47,990 --> 00:54:50,310
A leaf came loose from one of the tall trees,

1352
00:54:50,810 --> 00:54:53,790
and fell on the hood of the car with a lightness that seemed calculated.

1353
00:54:54,510 --> 00:54:55,410
No one said anything.

1354
00:54:55,870 --> 00:54:57,010
I don't know if I can.

1355
00:54:57,370 --> 00:54:58,030
Kitt said, low.

1356
00:54:58,470 --> 00:54:59,550
You can make it to the door.

1357
00:55:00,090 --> 00:55:00,990
After that we decide.

1358
00:55:01,590 --> 00:55:04,030
And if they hate me, they don't hate you.

1359
00:55:04,030 --> 00:55:05,810
They don't know how to hate you.

1360
00:55:06,050 --> 00:55:06,850
Kitt didn't answer.

1361
00:55:07,250 --> 00:55:09,070
The open the car door and got out slowly.

1362
00:55:09,510 --> 00:55:12,410
Like someone stepping onto a floor that might not hold his weight.

1363
00:55:12,870 --> 00:55:15,630
The main hall smelled of Magnolia and old money.

1364
00:55:16,070 --> 00:55:19,470
The afternoon came in through the tall windows in bands of golden light,

1365
00:55:19,790 --> 00:55:22,610
that crossed the marble and stopped at the empty chair near the window,

1366
00:55:23,030 --> 00:55:24,850
as if they knew exactly where to land.

1367
00:55:25,370 --> 00:55:26,610
Rowena went in first.

1368
00:55:27,070 --> 00:55:28,850
She deliberately chose that place.

1369
00:55:29,290 --> 00:55:31,950
Not the living room, not the library, not J. Go's study.

1370
00:55:31,950 --> 00:55:34,270
Where everything had begun to fall apart.

1371
00:55:34,730 --> 00:55:35,230
The hall.

1372
00:55:35,810 --> 00:55:38,050
The same room where one night, month earlier,

1373
00:55:38,670 --> 00:55:41,990
a woman in a borrowed dress had held the face of a silent man

1374
00:55:41,990 --> 00:55:44,470
and kissed him in front of 300 people.

1375
00:55:44,870 --> 00:55:45,970
The smell was the same.

1376
00:55:46,450 --> 00:55:48,250
The light came in at the same angle.

1377
00:55:48,830 --> 00:55:50,050
The chair was still empty.

1378
00:55:50,690 --> 00:55:54,130
Rowena positioned herself exactly where she had stood on that other night.

1379
00:55:54,470 --> 00:55:56,650
As if she were marking a fixed point on a map,

1380
00:55:57,150 --> 00:55:58,590
only she knew how to read.

1381
00:55:59,070 --> 00:56:00,570
Kitt stayed one step behind,

1382
00:56:00,570 --> 00:56:04,970
still in his cap, still with his hand closed around the strap of the backpack.

1383
00:56:05,530 --> 00:56:06,910
Feline opened the double doors.

1384
00:56:07,490 --> 00:56:08,690
Yudora came in first.

1385
00:56:09,050 --> 00:56:10,570
The matriarch noticed Rowena,

1386
00:56:11,130 --> 00:56:12,650
noticed the figure behind her.

1387
00:56:12,930 --> 00:56:15,410
And for a moment, tiny, almost invisible,

1388
00:56:16,050 --> 00:56:18,010
her spine seemed to give way a millimeter.

1389
00:56:18,630 --> 00:56:19,650
She restrained it.

1390
00:56:19,830 --> 00:56:21,050
She kept her chin high.

1391
00:56:21,370 --> 00:56:23,910
She crossed the hall to the center and stopped, waiting.

1392
00:56:24,530 --> 00:56:27,850
J. Go came in after, and his world stopped turning.

1393
00:56:27,850 --> 00:56:30,170
There was a thin man in the hall.

1394
00:56:30,630 --> 00:56:34,850
Then, with his cap pulled low, a small scar on his eyebrow,

1395
00:56:35,330 --> 00:56:38,050
his shoulders narrower than memory had drawn them.

1396
00:56:38,290 --> 00:56:40,290
A man who slowly lowered the cap,

1397
00:56:40,670 --> 00:56:43,190
revealing his short hair, and looked up.

1398
00:56:43,370 --> 00:56:45,690
And it was the gaze of the 18-year-old boy,

1399
00:56:46,050 --> 00:56:48,670
who had taken a boat out alone on a stormy night,

1400
00:56:48,930 --> 00:56:50,050
ten years before.

1401
00:56:50,450 --> 00:56:53,430
J. Go said nothing for a length of time, no one there could measure.

1402
00:56:53,890 --> 00:56:55,190
He took a step than another.

1403
00:56:55,650 --> 00:56:56,270
Then he stopped.

1404
00:56:56,270 --> 00:56:59,210
Inside it was as if a dam had given way.

1405
00:56:59,610 --> 00:57:02,110
The old guilt, the anguish of the last two days,

1406
00:57:02,630 --> 00:57:07,530
the fear of losing Rowena, all mixing into a single hot point in the middle of his chest,

1407
00:57:07,890 --> 00:57:09,750
too hot to be born with composure.

1408
00:57:10,110 --> 00:57:11,270
He felt his throat tightened.

1409
00:57:11,730 --> 00:57:13,330
He felt his hands go cold.

1410
00:57:13,750 --> 00:57:16,610
He felt with brutal clarity that the punishment hadn't come.

1411
00:57:16,970 --> 00:57:20,450
That life, against any deserving, had given something back.

1412
00:57:20,810 --> 00:57:21,750
Kit, he said.

1413
00:57:22,210 --> 00:57:24,230
And his voice came out choked, ridiculous.

1414
00:57:24,230 --> 00:57:27,510
The voice of a big boy that didn't fit that man.

1415
00:57:27,970 --> 00:57:30,350
Kit, Kit dropped the backpack on the floor.

1416
00:57:30,790 --> 00:57:32,490
The thud was dry on the marble.

1417
00:57:32,990 --> 00:57:35,870
I ran away, he said, and his mouth trembled.

1418
00:57:36,350 --> 00:57:39,150
I ran away because I thought I wasn't important to anyone.

1419
00:57:39,650 --> 00:57:40,890
J. Go closed his eyes.

1420
00:57:41,490 --> 00:57:44,590
A tear fell before he could command his body to hold it back.

1421
00:57:44,910 --> 00:57:46,950
Then another. He didn't wipe them.

1422
00:57:47,190 --> 00:57:51,710
I spent ten years, he answered, trying to fix the worst choice of my life.

1423
00:57:51,710 --> 00:57:55,470
Kit shook his head incredulous, and the shaking became a tremor,

1424
00:57:55,890 --> 00:57:58,190
and the tremor became a short dry sob.

1425
00:57:58,750 --> 00:58:01,170
J. Go crossed the rest of the hall in three strides,

1426
00:58:01,510 --> 00:58:03,590
and hugged his brother any which way.

1427
00:58:04,070 --> 00:58:05,850
A crooked hug without elegance,

1428
00:58:06,370 --> 00:58:08,650
without the composure all of Savannah knew.

1429
00:58:08,930 --> 00:58:11,170
A hug that had waited ten years to happen,

1430
00:58:11,590 --> 00:58:14,790
and that now happened all at once, clumsy, and urgent.

1431
00:58:15,430 --> 00:58:16,850
Kit was slow to return it.

1432
00:58:17,230 --> 00:58:19,610
When he did, he gripped J. Go's coat,

1433
00:58:19,610 --> 00:58:22,050
as if he were holding on so as not to fall.

1434
00:58:22,490 --> 00:58:24,210
J. Go's coat at the back had stopped breathing.

1435
00:58:24,770 --> 00:58:29,250
The feared matriarch, the woman who demanded proof of love in the middle of a crowded hall,

1436
00:58:29,710 --> 00:58:33,350
the woman Roena had met with eyes of steel, took a step forward,

1437
00:58:33,870 --> 00:58:37,210
then another. And with no audience, without elegance,

1438
00:58:37,630 --> 00:58:40,630
without any of the posture all of Savannah knew by heart,

1439
00:58:41,010 --> 00:58:44,250
J. Go's coat on the marble floor beside her lost son.

1440
00:58:44,530 --> 00:58:46,770
The tweed dress folded like an old cloth.

1441
00:58:46,770 --> 00:58:50,750
A hand sought Kit's face without the courage to touch it right away.

1442
00:58:51,050 --> 00:58:55,070
My boy, she said, and the knife-edged voice became a voice with no edge.

1443
00:58:55,570 --> 00:58:58,550
My boy, Kit turned to his mother and couldn't speak.

1444
00:58:58,970 --> 00:59:00,890
He just rested his forehead on her shoulder.

1445
00:59:01,490 --> 00:59:06,630
Udora closed her arms around her son with a care no one ever had seen that woman show.

1446
00:59:07,070 --> 00:59:08,390
Roena watched from the doorway,

1447
00:59:09,110 --> 00:59:11,810
inside she felt her body way from two sides at once.

1448
00:59:12,170 --> 00:59:15,370
There was relief, yes, the real, physical relief

1449
00:59:15,370 --> 00:59:19,130
of seeing the family finally occupy the space it needed to occupy.

1450
00:59:19,690 --> 00:59:22,170
And there was an exhaustion she hadn't noticed accumulate,

1451
00:59:22,830 --> 00:59:27,210
until the adrenaline dropped for good. The last 48 hours had taken everything,

1452
00:59:27,670 --> 00:59:31,030
and there was two something hard in the middle of her chest,

1453
00:59:31,450 --> 00:59:33,730
something that made her understand that this moment

1454
00:59:33,730 --> 00:59:36,850
belonged to those three and that she didn't need to sign it.

1455
00:59:37,030 --> 00:59:41,390
She took a step back, then another. She closed the double doors in silence.

1456
00:59:41,390 --> 00:59:46,210
The veranda facing the savanna river had a warm late afternoon wind,

1457
00:59:46,670 --> 00:59:48,930
Roena leaned against the cold stone parapet,

1458
00:59:49,210 --> 00:59:51,490
and watched the water dark and little by little.

1459
00:59:51,970 --> 00:59:55,190
The reflection of the light going away in wide slow bands.

1460
00:59:55,710 --> 00:59:59,250
She didn't cry. She felt inside her chest a new stillness,

1461
00:59:59,470 --> 01:00:02,130
the kind that only arrives after days that are too long,

1462
01:00:02,570 --> 01:00:06,230
when the body finally drops its guard because it has nowhere left to put the tension.

1463
01:00:06,750 --> 01:00:08,750
Jego found her there ten minutes later.

1464
01:00:08,750 --> 01:00:13,850
He'd washed his face, his suit was still rumpled. His eyes still red settled on her

1465
01:00:13,850 --> 01:00:16,150
before any words and stayed there. Heavy.

1466
01:00:16,710 --> 01:00:19,830
As if they needed to confirm that she was real and that she was standing,

1467
01:00:20,410 --> 01:00:23,170
he stopped three steps away. He didn't come closer.

1468
01:00:23,750 --> 01:00:27,930
Any word he realized would be too small. Any sentence would sound like a clause,

1469
01:00:28,510 --> 01:00:32,750
and he'd already spent six months signing clauses with her without asking permission for it.

1470
01:00:32,950 --> 01:00:37,550
So he stayed quiet. He just stood there, looking at her as if it were the first time.

1471
01:00:37,550 --> 01:00:42,630
You brought him. He said it last. I brought him. I don't know how to thank you.

1472
01:00:42,890 --> 01:00:45,490
Don't thank me. It's not the kind of thing you thank someone for.

1473
01:00:45,950 --> 01:00:50,490
He nodded, a nod that was almost a bow. The river below kept darkening,

1474
01:00:51,170 --> 01:00:55,350
indifferent to the weight of that veranda. A girl crossed the sky in a lazy arc.

1475
01:00:55,850 --> 01:00:59,550
Ruinna felt the warmth of his body near hers without needing to look to be sure.

1476
01:00:59,910 --> 01:01:07,530
There was magnetism there. The same as always. The same that had risen up her back on a

1477
01:01:07,530 --> 01:01:12,630
beside him. There was a new distance. A distance she decided to preserve for now.

1478
01:01:12,890 --> 01:01:19,510
I need to sleep alone tonight. She said, Jego took a second. He didn't protest. He didn't make a face.

1479
01:01:19,850 --> 01:01:25,870
He didn't embed any request disguised as agreement. That's fine. Ruinna turned her face to him.

1480
01:01:26,150 --> 01:01:30,910
It's the first time in six months you've given me an answer without packaging. He almost smiled.

1481
01:01:31,470 --> 01:01:37,110
Almost. I'm learning. He answered. Very low. There was exhaustion in his face.

1482
01:01:37,110 --> 01:01:42,070
But there was also something open she'd never seen there before. He wasn't the man of ice.

1483
01:01:42,450 --> 01:01:47,850
He wasn't the man of calculated control. He was a man who had seen his brother alive after 10

1484
01:01:47,850 --> 01:01:53,210
years and no longer knew what to do with his own chest. Tomorrow will talk. She said,

1485
01:01:53,670 --> 01:01:59,590
Tomorrow I'll ask. He said, if you'll let me. She nodded. He raised his hand toward her face,

1486
01:02:00,030 --> 01:02:05,070
stopped halfway and lowered his arm. The interrupted gesture weighed more than the touch would have

1487
01:02:05,810 --> 01:02:11,090
Ruinna inside understood that he had understood. She went down the veranda stairs without hurry.

1488
01:02:11,650 --> 01:02:16,590
Feline took her to the house near the river. Jego went back inside to the family he had forgotten

1489
01:02:16,590 --> 01:02:21,270
how to embrace without a contract. That night in the kitchen of the house near the river,

1490
01:02:21,730 --> 01:02:26,470
Ruinna drank a glass of water in silence and looked at the phone on the table. There were no

1491
01:02:26,470 --> 01:02:31,890
messages. For the first time in six months, no one knew where she was because no one had been put in

1492
01:02:31,890 --> 01:02:36,710
place to know. She turned off the kitchen light and the darkness arrived with a calm that seemed

1493
01:02:36,710 --> 01:02:42,090
at last deserved. On the other side of the city, in a room he hadn't been in for 10 years,

1494
01:02:42,590 --> 01:02:47,890
Jego quint personally made up his brother's bed, folded the blanket, opened the window two

1495
01:02:47,890 --> 01:02:53,750
fingers to let the air in, and sat on the hallway floor until dawn, with the door a jar listening

1496
01:02:53,750 --> 01:02:58,930
to kit sleep. Sunday morning arrived at the house near the Savannah River, with a low,

1497
01:02:58,930 --> 01:03:03,310
wary light that came through the cracks in the curtains, like someone asking permission.

1498
01:03:03,910 --> 01:03:09,310
Ruinna was in the kitchen. Barefoot, with a cold mug in her hands, she hadn't slept well.

1499
01:03:09,650 --> 01:03:15,130
The two wide bed had felt wide in a new way, without anger and without peace, only with a

1500
01:03:15,130 --> 01:03:20,290
question waiting for its answer outside the door. She heard the engine before she heard the foot steps.

1501
01:03:20,810 --> 01:03:25,370
A car stopped on the gravel. The door closed with the care of someone who knew the whole house

1502
01:03:25,370 --> 01:03:30,290
was listening. Jego appeared in the kitchen doorway, with the cream envelope open in his hand.

1503
01:03:30,750 --> 01:03:35,390
He had no jacket. He had the rumpled shirt of someone who'd spent the night sitting on a hallway

1504
01:03:35,390 --> 01:03:41,030
floor. He stopped two steps from her, as if asking permission to cross that last stretch of

1505
01:03:41,030 --> 01:03:47,770
floor. May I? He asked. Ruinna nodded. He came. He set the envelope on the table between them,

1506
01:03:47,890 --> 01:03:53,190
facing her. The letter was already unfolded inside. She recognized the letter head, the header,

1507
01:03:53,190 --> 01:03:58,490
the short paragraph that month's earlier had been intercepted before reaching her. They wanted

1508
01:03:58,490 --> 01:04:04,470
you for a series of long reports, Jego said, his voice low almost crumpled. In depth investigation

1509
01:04:04,470 --> 01:04:09,970
no short deadline. Your by-line on every piece I read it when it came. I answered for you.

1510
01:04:10,150 --> 01:04:14,810
I wrote with thanks no. I lied about it every day since. She looked at the letter.

1511
01:04:15,310 --> 01:04:19,750
Then at his face. Jego was pale in a way different from the night of the phone call.

1512
01:04:19,750 --> 01:04:24,810
That whiteness wasn't fear of what she'd find out. It was shame at what he'd done.

1513
01:04:25,190 --> 01:04:31,010
Why, Ruinna asked without sharpness? Just needing to hear it. Because I was afraid you'd accept,

1514
01:04:31,390 --> 01:04:36,970
